56smt2_convt::smt2_convt(
57 const namespacet &_ns,
58 const std::string &_benchmark,
59 const std::string &_notes,
60 const std::string &_logic,
61 solvert _solver,
62 std::ostream &_out)
63 : use_FPA_theory(false),
64 use_array_of_bool(false),
65 use_as_const(false),
66 use_check_sat_assuming(false),
67 use_datatypes(false),
68 use_lambda_for_array(false),
69 emit_set_logic(true),
70 ns(_ns),
71 out(_out),
72 benchmark(_benchmark),
73 notes(_notes),
74 logic(_logic),
75 solver(_solver),
76 boolbv_width(_ns),
77 pointer_logic(_ns),
78 no_boolean_variables(0)
79{
80 // We set some defaults differently
81 // for some solvers.
82
83 switch(solver)
84 {
85 case solvert::GENERIC:
86 break;
87
88 case solvert::BITWUZLA:
89 use_FPA_theory = true;
90 use_array_of_bool = true;
91 use_as_const = true;
92 use_check_sat_assuming = true;
93 use_lambda_for_array = false;
94 emit_set_logic = false;
95 break;
96
97 case solvert::BOOLECTOR:
98 break;
99
100 case solvert::CPROVER_SMT2:
101 use_FPA_theory = true;
102 use_array_of_bool = true;
103 use_as_const = true;
104 use_check_sat_assuming = true;
105 emit_set_logic = false;
106 break;
107
108 case solvert::CVC3:
109 break;
110
111 case solvert::CVC4:
112 logic = "ALL";
113 use_array_of_bool = true;
114 use_as_const = true;
115 break;
116
117 case solvert::CVC5:
118 logic = "ALL";
119 use_FPA_theory = true;
120 use_array_of_bool = true;
121 use_as_const = true;
122 use_check_sat_assuming = true;
123 use_datatypes = true;
124 break;
125
126 case solvert::MATHSAT:
127 break;
128
129 case solvert::YICES:
130 break;
131
132 case solvert::Z3:
133 use_array_of_bool = true;
134 use_as_const = true;
135 use_check_sat_assuming = true;
136 use_lambda_for_array = true;
137 emit_set_logic = false;
138 use_datatypes = true;
139 break;
140 }
141
142 write_header();
143}

160tvt smt2_convt::l_get(literalt l) const
161{
162 if(l.is_true())
163 return tvt(true);
164 if(l.is_false())
165 return tvt(false);
166
167 INVARIANT(
168 l.var_no() < boolean_assignment.size(),
169 "variable number shall be within bounds");
170 return tvt(boolean_assignment[l.var_no()]^l.sign());
171}

173void smt2_convt::write_header()
174{
175 out << "; SMT 2" << "\n";
176
177 switch(solver)
178 {
179 // clang-format off
180 case solvert::GENERIC: break;
181 case solvert::BITWUZLA: out << "; Generated for Bitwuzla\n"; break;
182 case solvert::BOOLECTOR: out << "; Generated for Boolector\n"; break;
183 case solvert::CPROVER_SMT2:
184 out << "; Generated for the CPROVER SMT2 solver\n"; break;
185 case solvert::CVC3: out << "; Generated for CVC 3\n"; break;
186 case solvert::CVC4: out << "; Generated for CVC 4\n"; break;
187 case solvert::CVC5: out << "; Generated for CVC 5\n"; break;
188 case solvert::MATHSAT: out << "; Generated for MathSAT\n"; break;
189 case solvert::YICES: out << "; Generated for Yices\n"; break;
190 case solvert::Z3: out << "; Generated for Z3\n"; break;
191 // clang-format on
192 }
193
194 out << "(set-info :source \"" << notes << "\")" << "\n";
195
196 out << "(set-option :produce-models true)" << "\n";
197
198 // We use a broad mixture of logics, so on some solvers
199 // its better not to declare here.
200 // set-logic should come after setting options
201 if(emit_set_logic && !logic.empty())
202 out << "(set-logic " << logic << ")" << "\n";
203}
204
205void smt2_convt::write_footer()
206{
207 out << "\n";
208
209 // fix up the object sizes
210 for(const auto &object : object_sizes)
211 define_object_size(object.second, object.first);
212
213 if(use_check_sat_assuming && !assumptions.empty())
214 {
215 out << "(check-sat-assuming (";
216 for(const auto &assumption : assumptions)
217 convert_literal(assumption);
218 out << "))\n";
219 }
220 else
221 {
222 // add the assumptions, if any
223 if(!assumptions.empty())
224 {
225 out << "; assumptions\n";
226
227 for(const auto &assumption : assumptions)
228 {
229 out << "(assert ";
230 convert_literal(assumption);
231 out << ")"
232 << "\n";
233 }
234 }
235
236 out << "(check-sat)\n";
237 }
238
239 out << "\n";
240
241 if(solver!=solvert::BOOLECTOR)
242 {
243 for(const auto &id : smt2_identifiers)
244 out << "(get-value (" << id << "))"
245 << "\n";
246 }
247
248 out << "\n";
249
250 out << "(exit)\n";
251
252 out << "; end of SMT2 file"
253 << "\n";
254}

257static bool is_zero_width(const typet &type, const namespacet &ns)
258{
259 if(type.id() == ID_empty)
260 return true;
261 else if(type.id() == ID_struct_tag)
262 return is_zero_width(ns.follow_tag(to_struct_tag_type(type)), ns);
263 else if(type.id() == ID_union_tag)
264 return is_zero_width(ns.follow_tag(to_union_tag_type(type)), ns);
265 else if(type.id() == ID_struct || type.id() == ID_union)
266 {
267 for(const auto &comp : to_struct_union_type(type).components())
268 {
269 if(!is_zero_width(comp.type(), ns))
270 return false;
271 }
272 return true;
273 }
274 else if(auto array_type = type_try_dynamic_cast<array_typet>(type))
275 {
276 // we ignore array_type->size().is_zero() for now as there may be
277 // out-of-bounds accesses that we need to model
278 return is_zero_width(array_type->element_type(), ns);
279 }
280 else
281 return false;
282}

284void smt2_convt::define_object_size(
285 const irep_idt &id,
286 const object_size_exprt &expr)
287{
288 const exprt &ptr = expr.pointer();
289 std::size_t pointer_width = boolbv_width(ptr.type());
290 std::size_t number = 0;
291 std::size_t h=pointer_width-1;
292 std::size_t l=pointer_width-config.bv_encoding.object_bits;
293
294 for(const auto &o : pointer_logic.objects)
295 {
296 const typet &type = o.type();
297 auto size_expr = size_of_expr(type, ns);
298
299 if(
300 (o.id() != ID_symbol && o.id() != ID_string_constant) ||
301 !size_expr.has_value())
302 {
303 ++number;
304 continue;
305 }
306
307 find_symbols(*size_expr);
308 out << "(assert (=> (= "
309 << "((_ extract " << h << " " << l << ") ";
310 convert_expr(ptr);
311 out << ") (_ bv" << number << " " << config.bv_encoding.object_bits << "))"
312 << "(= " << id << " ";
313 convert_expr(*size_expr);
314 out << ")))\n";
315
316 ++number;
317 }
318}

320decision_proceduret::resultt smt2_convt::dec_solve(const exprt &assumption)
321{
322 if(assumption.is_nil())
323 write_footer();
324 else
325 {
326 assumptions.push_back(convert(assumption));
327 write_footer();
328 assumptions.pop_back();
329 }
330
331 out.flush();
332 return decision_proceduret::resultt::D_ERROR;
333}

335exprt smt2_convt::get(const exprt &expr) const
336{
337 if(expr.id()==ID_symbol)
338 {
339 const irep_idt &id=to_symbol_expr(expr).get_identifier();
340
341 identifier_mapt::const_iterator it=identifier_map.find(id);
342
343 if(it!=identifier_map.end())
344 return it->second.value;
345 return expr;
346 }
347 else if(expr.id()==ID_nondet_symbol)
348 {
349 const irep_idt &id=to_nondet_symbol_expr(expr).get_identifier();
350
351 identifier_mapt::const_iterator it=identifier_map.find(id);
352
353 if(it!=identifier_map.end())
354 return it->second.value;
355 }
356 else if(expr.id() == ID_literal)
357 {
358 auto l = to_literal_expr(expr).get_literal();
359 if(l_get(l).is_true())
360 return true_exprt();
361 else
362 return false_exprt();
363 }
364 else if(expr.id() == ID_not)
365 {
366 auto op = get(to_not_expr(expr).op());
367 if(op.is_true())
368 return false_exprt();
369 else if(op.is_false())
370 return true_exprt();
371 }
372 else if(
373 expr.is_constant() || expr.id() == ID_empty_union ||
374 (!expr.has_operands() && (expr.id() == ID_struct || expr.id() == ID_array)))
375 {
376 return expr;
377 }
378 else if(expr.has_operands())
379 {
380 exprt copy = expr;
381 for(auto &op : copy.operands())
382 {
383 exprt eval_op = get(op);
384 if(eval_op.is_nil())
385 return nil_exprt{};
386 op = std::move(eval_op);
387 }
388 return copy;
389 }
390
391 return nil_exprt();
392}

394constant_exprt smt2_convt::parse_literal(
395 const irept &src,
396 const typet &type)
397{
398 // See http://www.grammatech.com/resources/smt/SMTLIBTutorial.pdf for the
399 // syntax of SMTlib2 literals.
400 //
401 // A literal expression is one of the following forms:
402 //
403 // * Numeral -- this is a natural number in decimal and is of the form:
404 // 0|([1-9][0-9]*)
405 // * Decimal -- this is a decimal expansion of a real number of the form:
406 // (0|[1-9][0-9]*)[.]([0-9]+)
407 // * Binary -- this is a natural number in binary and is of the form:
408 // #b[01]+
409 // * Hex -- this is a natural number in hexadecimal and is of the form:
410 // #x[0-9a-fA-F]+
411 //
412 // Right now I'm not parsing decimals. It'd be nice if we had a real YACC
413 // parser here, but whatever.
414
415 mp_integer value;
416
417 if(!src.id().empty())
418 {
419 const std::string &s=src.id_string();
420
421 if(s.size()>=2 && s[0]=='#' && s[1]=='b')
422 {
423 // Binary #b010101
424 value=string2integer(s.substr(2), 2);
425 }
426 else if(s.size()>=2 && s[0]=='#' && s[1]=='x')
427 {
428 // Hex #x012345
429 value=string2integer(s.substr(2), 16);
430 }
431 else
432 {
433 // Numeral
434 value=string2integer(s);
435 }
436 }
437 else if(src.get_sub().size()==2 &&
438 src.get_sub()[0].id()=="-") // (- 100)
439 {
440 value=-string2integer(src.get_sub()[1].id_string());
441 }
442 else if(src.get_sub().size()==3 &&
443 src.get_sub()[0].id()=="_" &&
444 // (_ bvDECIMAL_VALUE SIZE)
445 src.get_sub()[1].id_string().substr(0, 2)=="bv")
446 {
447 value=string2integer(src.get_sub()[1].id_string().substr(2));
448 }
449 else if(src.get_sub().size()==4 &&
450 src.get_sub()[0].id()=="fp") // (fp signbv exponentbv significandbv)
451 {
452 if(type.id()==ID_floatbv)
453 {
454 const floatbv_typet &floatbv_type=to_floatbv_type(type);
455 constant_exprt s1 = parse_literal(src.get_sub()[1], unsignedbv_typet(1));
456 constant_exprt s2 =
457 parse_literal(src.get_sub()[2], unsignedbv_typet(floatbv_type.get_e()));
458 constant_exprt s3 =
459 parse_literal(src.get_sub()[3], unsignedbv_typet(floatbv_type.get_f()));
460
461 const auto s1_int = numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(s1);
462 const auto s2_int = numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(s2);
463 const auto s3_int = numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(s3);
464
465 // stitch the bits together
466 value = bitwise_or(
467 s1_int << (floatbv_type.get_e() + floatbv_type.get_f()),
468 bitwise_or((s2_int << floatbv_type.get_f()), s3_int));
469 }
470 else
471 value=0;
472 }
473 else if(src.get_sub().size()==4 &&
474 src.get_sub()[0].id()=="_" &&
475 src.get_sub()[1].id()=="+oo") // (_ +oo e s)
476 {
477 std::size_t e = unsafe_string2size_t(src.get_sub()[2].id_string());
478 std::size_t s = unsafe_string2size_t(src.get_sub()[3].id_string());
479 return ieee_floatt::plus_infinity(ieee_float_spect(s - 1, e)).to_expr();
480 }
481 else if(src.get_sub().size()==4 &&
482 src.get_sub()[0].id()=="_" &&
483 src.get_sub()[1].id()=="-oo") // (_ -oo e s)
484 {
485 std::size_t e = unsafe_string2size_t(src.get_sub()[2].id_string());
486 std::size_t s = unsafe_string2size_t(src.get_sub()[3].id_string());
487 return ieee_floatt::minus_infinity(ieee_float_spect(s - 1, e)).to_expr();
488 }
489 else if(src.get_sub().size()==4 &&
490 src.get_sub()[0].id()=="_" &&
491 src.get_sub()[1].id()=="NaN") // (_ NaN e s)
492 {
493 std::size_t e = unsafe_string2size_t(src.get_sub()[2].id_string());
494 std::size_t s = unsafe_string2size_t(src.get_sub()[3].id_string());
495 return ieee_floatt::NaN(ieee_float_spect(s - 1, e)).to_expr();
496 }
497
498 if(type.id()==ID_signedbv ||
499 type.id()==ID_unsignedbv ||
500 type.id()==ID_c_enum ||
501 type.id()==ID_c_bool)
502 {
503 return from_integer(value, type);
504 }
505 else if(type.id()==ID_c_enum_tag)
506 {
507 constant_exprt result =
508 from_integer(value, ns.follow_tag(to_c_enum_tag_type(type)));
509
510 // restore the c_enum_tag type
511 result.type() = type;
512 return result;
513 }
514 else if(type.id()==ID_fixedbv ||
515 type.id()==ID_floatbv)
516 {
517 std::size_t width=boolbv_width(type);
518 return constant_exprt(integer2bvrep(value, width), type);
519 }
520 else if(type.id()==ID_integer ||
521 type.id()==ID_range)
522 {
523 return from_integer(value, type);
524 }
525 else
526 UNREACHABLE_BECAUSE(
527 "smt2_convt::parse_literal should not be of unsupported type " +
528 type.id_string());
529}

531exprt smt2_convt::parse_array(
532 const irept &src,
533 const array_typet &type)
534{
535 std::unordered_map<int64_t, exprt> operands_map;
536 walk_array_tree(&operands_map, src, type);
537 exprt::operandst operands;
538 // Try to find the default value, if there is none then set it
539 auto maybe_default_op = operands_map.find(-1);
540 exprt default_op;
541 if(maybe_default_op == operands_map.end())
542 default_op = nil_exprt();
543 else
544 default_op = maybe_default_op->second;
545 int64_t i = 0;
546 auto maybe_size = numeric_cast<std::int64_t>(type.size());
547 if(maybe_size.has_value())
548 {
549 while(i < maybe_size.value())
550 {
551 auto found_op = operands_map.find(i);
552 if(found_op != operands_map.end())
553 operands.emplace_back(found_op->second);
554 else
555 operands.emplace_back(default_op);
556 i++;
557 }
558 }
559 else
560 {
561 // Array size is unknown, keep adding with known indexes in order
562 // until we fail to find one.
563 auto found_op = operands_map.find(i);
564 while(found_op != operands_map.end())
565 {
566 operands.emplace_back(found_op->second);
567 i++;
568 found_op = operands_map.find(i);
569 }
570 operands.emplace_back(default_op);
571 }
572 return array_exprt(operands, type);
573}
574
575void smt2_convt::walk_array_tree(
576 std::unordered_map<int64_t, exprt> *operands_map,
577 const irept &src,
578 const array_typet &type)
579{
580 if(src.get_sub().size()==4 && src.get_sub()[0].id()=="store")
581 {
582 // This is the SMT syntax being parsed here
583 // (store array index value)
584 // Recurse
585 walk_array_tree(operands_map, src.get_sub()[1], type);
586 const auto index_expr = parse_rec(src.get_sub()[2], type.size().type());
587 const constant_exprt index_constant = to_constant_expr(index_expr);
588 mp_integer tempint;
589 bool failure = to_integer(index_constant, tempint);
590 if(failure)
591 return;
592 long index = tempint.to_long();
593 exprt value = parse_rec(src.get_sub()[3], type.element_type());
594 operands_map->emplace(index, value);
595 }
596 else if(src.get_sub().size()==2 &&
597 src.get_sub()[0].get_sub().size()==3 &&
598 src.get_sub()[0].get_sub()[0].id()=="as" &&
599 src.get_sub()[0].get_sub()[1].id()=="const")
600 {
601 // (as const type_info default_value)
602 exprt default_value = parse_rec(src.get_sub()[1], type.element_type());
603 operands_map->emplace(-1, default_value);
604 }
605 else
606 {
607 auto bindings_it = current_bindings.find(src.id());
608 if(bindings_it != current_bindings.end())
609 walk_array_tree(operands_map, bindings_it->second, type);
610 }
611}

613exprt smt2_convt::parse_union(
614 const irept &src,
615 const union_typet &type)
616{
617 // these are always flat
618 PRECONDITION(!type.components().empty());
619 const union_typet::componentt &first=type.components().front();
620 std::size_t width=boolbv_width(type);
621 exprt value = parse_rec(src, unsignedbv_typet(width));
622 if(value.is_nil())
623 return nil_exprt();
624 const typecast_exprt converted(value, first.type());
625 return union_exprt(first.get_name(), converted, type);
626}

628struct_exprt
629smt2_convt::parse_struct(const irept &src, const struct_typet &type)
630{
631 const struct_typet::componentst &components =
632 type.components();
633
634 struct_exprt result(exprt::operandst(components.size(), nil_exprt()), type);
635
636 if(components.empty())
637 return result;
638
639 if(use_datatypes)
640 {
641 // Structs look like:
642 // (mk-struct.1 <component0> <component1> ... <componentN>)
643 std::size_t j = 1;
644 for(std::size_t i=0; i<components.size(); i++)
645 {
646 const struct_typet::componentt &c=components[i];
647 if(is_zero_width(components[i].type(), ns))
648 {
649 result.operands()[i] = nil_exprt{};
650 }
651 else
652 {
653 DATA_INVARIANT(
654 src.get_sub().size() > j, "insufficient number of component values");
655 result.operands()[i] = parse_rec(src.get_sub()[j], c.type());
656 ++j;
657 }
658 }
659 }
660 else
661 {
662 // These are just flattened, i.e., we expect to see a monster bit vector.
663 std::size_t total_width=boolbv_width(type);
664 const auto l = parse_literal(src, unsignedbv_typet(total_width));
665
666 const irep_idt binary =
667 integer2binary(numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(l), total_width);
668
669 CHECK_RETURN(binary.size() == total_width);
670
671 std::size_t offset=0;
672
673 for(std::size_t i=0; i<components.size(); i++)
674 {
675 if(is_zero_width(components[i].type(), ns))
676 continue;
677
678 std::size_t component_width=boolbv_width(components[i].type());
679
680 INVARIANT(
681 offset + component_width <= total_width,
682 "struct component bits shall be within struct bit vector");
683
684 std::string component_binary=
685 "#b"+id2string(binary).substr(
686 total_width-offset-component_width, component_width);
687
688 result.operands()[i]=
689 parse_rec(irept(component_binary), components[i].type());
690
691 offset+=component_width;
692 }
693 }
694
695 return result;
696}

698exprt smt2_convt::parse_rec(const irept &src, const typet &type)
699{
700 if(src.get_sub().size() == 3 && src.get_sub()[0].id() == ID_let)
701 {
702 // This is produced by Z3
703 // (let (....) (....))
704 auto previous_bindings = current_bindings;
705 for(const auto &binding : src.get_sub()[1].get_sub())
706 {
707 const irep_idt &name = binding.get_sub()[0].id();
708 current_bindings.emplace(name, binding.get_sub()[1]);
709 }
710 exprt result = parse_rec(src.get_sub()[2], type);
711 current_bindings = std::move(previous_bindings);
712 return result;
713 }
714
715 auto bindings_it = current_bindings.find(src.id());
716 if(bindings_it != current_bindings.end())
717 {
718 return parse_rec(bindings_it->second, type);
719 }
720
721 if(
722 type.id() == ID_signedbv || type.id() == ID_unsignedbv ||
723 type.id() == ID_integer || type.id() == ID_rational ||
724 type.id() == ID_real || type.id() == ID_c_enum ||
725 type.id() == ID_c_enum_tag || type.id() == ID_fixedbv ||
726 type.id() == ID_floatbv || type.id() == ID_c_bool || type.id() == ID_range)
727 {
728 return parse_literal(src, type);
729 }
730 else if(type.id()==ID_bool)
731 {
732 if(src.id()==ID_1 || src.id()==ID_true)
733 return true_exprt();
734 else if(src.id()==ID_0 || src.id()==ID_false)
735 return false_exprt();
736 }
737 else if(type.id()==ID_pointer)
738 {
739 // these come in as bit-vector literals
740 std::size_t width=boolbv_width(type);
741 constant_exprt bv_expr = parse_literal(src, unsignedbv_typet(width));
742
743 mp_integer v = numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(bv_expr);
744
745 // split into object and offset
746 mp_integer pow=power(2, width-config.bv_encoding.object_bits);
747 pointer_logict::pointert ptr{numeric_cast_v<std::size_t>(v / pow), v % pow};
748 return annotated_pointer_constant_exprt(
749 bv_expr.get_value(),
750 pointer_logic.pointer_expr(ptr, to_pointer_type(type)));
751 }
752 else if(type.id()==ID_struct)
753 {
754 return parse_struct(src, to_struct_type(type));
755 }
756 else if(type.id() == ID_struct_tag)
757 {
758 auto struct_expr =
759 parse_struct(src, ns.follow_tag(to_struct_tag_type(type)));
760 // restore the tag type
761 struct_expr.type() = type;
762 return std::move(struct_expr);
763 }
764 else if(type.id()==ID_union)
765 {
766 return parse_union(src, to_union_type(type));
767 }
768 else if(type.id() == ID_union_tag)
769 {
770 auto union_expr = parse_union(src, ns.follow_tag(to_union_tag_type(type)));
771 // restore the tag type
772 union_expr.type() = type;
773 return union_expr;
774 }
775 else if(type.id()==ID_array)
776 {
777 return parse_array(src, to_array_type(type));
778 }
779
780 return nil_exprt();
781}
782
783void smt2_convt::convert_address_of_rec(
784 const exprt &expr,
785 const pointer_typet &result_type)
786{
787 if(
788 expr.id() == ID_symbol || expr.is_constant() ||
789 expr.id() == ID_string_constant || expr.id() == ID_label)
790 {
791 const std::size_t object_bits = config.bv_encoding.object_bits;
792 const std::size_t max_objects = std::size_t(1) << object_bits;
793 const mp_integer object_id = pointer_logic.add_object(expr);
794
795 if(object_id >= max_objects)
796 {
797 throw analysis_exceptiont{
798 "too many addressed objects: maximum number of objects is set to 2^n=" +
799 std::to_string(max_objects) +
800 " (with n=" + std::to_string(object_bits) + "); " +
801 "use the `--object-bits n` option to increase the maximum number"};
802 }
803
804 out << "(concat (_ bv" << object_id << " " << object_bits << ")"
805 << " (_ bv0 " << boolbv_width(result_type) - object_bits << "))";
806 }
807 else if(expr.id()==ID_index)
808 {
809 const index_exprt &index_expr = to_index_expr(expr);
810
811 const exprt &array = index_expr.array();
812 const exprt &index = index_expr.index();
813
814 if(index.is_zero())
815 {
816 if(array.type().id()==ID_pointer)
817 convert_expr(array);
818 else if(array.type().id()==ID_array)
819 convert_address_of_rec(array, result_type);
820 else
821 UNREACHABLE;
822 }
823 else
824 {
825 // this is really pointer arithmetic
826 index_exprt new_index_expr = index_expr;
827 new_index_expr.index() = from_integer(0, index.type());
828
829 address_of_exprt address_of_expr(
830 new_index_expr,
831 pointer_type(to_array_type(array.type()).element_type()));
832
833 plus_exprt plus_expr{address_of_expr, index};
834
835 convert_expr(plus_expr);
836 }
837 }
838 else if(expr.id()==ID_member)
839 {
840 const member_exprt &member_expr=to_member_expr(expr);
841
842 const exprt &struct_op=member_expr.struct_op();
843 const typet &struct_op_type = struct_op.type();
844
845 DATA_INVARIANT(
846 struct_op_type.id() == ID_struct || struct_op_type.id() == ID_struct_tag,
847 "member expression operand shall have struct type");
848
849 const struct_typet &struct_type =
850 struct_op_type.id() == ID_struct_tag
851 ? ns.follow_tag(to_struct_tag_type(struct_op_type))
852 : to_struct_type(struct_op_type);
853
854 const irep_idt &component_name = member_expr.get_component_name();
855
856 const auto offset = member_offset(struct_type, component_name, ns);
857 CHECK_RETURN(offset.has_value() && *offset >= 0);
858
859 unsignedbv_typet index_type(boolbv_width(result_type));
860
861 // pointer arithmetic
862 out << "(bvadd ";
863 convert_address_of_rec(struct_op, result_type);
864 convert_expr(from_integer(*offset, index_type));
865 out << ")"; // bvadd
866 }
867 else if(expr.id()==ID_if)
868 {
869 const if_exprt &if_expr = to_if_expr(expr);
870
871 out << "(ite ";
872 convert_expr(if_expr.cond());
873 out << " ";
874 convert_address_of_rec(if_expr.true_case(), result_type);
875 out << " ";
876 convert_address_of_rec(if_expr.false_case(), result_type);
877 out << ")";
878 }
879 else
880 INVARIANT(
881 false,
882 "operand of address of expression should not be of kind " +
883 expr.id_string());
884}
885
886static bool has_quantifier(const exprt &expr)
887{
888 bool result = false;
889 expr.visit_post([&result](const exprt &node) {
890 if(node.id() == ID_exists || node.id() == ID_forall)
891 result = true;
892 });
893 return result;
894}
895
896literalt smt2_convt::convert(const exprt &expr)
897{
898 PRECONDITION(expr.is_boolean());
899
900 // Three cases where no new handle is needed.
901
902 if(expr.is_true())
903 return const_literal(true);
904 else if(expr.is_false())
905 return const_literal(false);
906 else if(expr.id()==ID_literal)
907 return to_literal_expr(expr).get_literal();
908
909 // Need a new handle
910
911 out << "\n";
912
913 exprt prepared_expr = prepare_for_convert_expr(expr);
914
915 literalt l(no_boolean_variables, false);
916 no_boolean_variables++;
917
918 out << "; convert\n";
919 out << "; Converting var_no " << l.var_no() << " with expr ID of "
920 << expr.id_string() << "\n";
921 // We're converting the expression, so store it in the defined_expressions
922 // store and in future we use the literal instead of the whole expression
923 // Note that here we are always converting, so we do not need to consider
924 // other literal kinds, only "|B###|"
925
926 // Z3 refuses get-value when a defined symbol contains a quantifier.
927 if(has_quantifier(prepared_expr))
928 {
929 out << "(declare-fun ";
930 convert_literal(l);
931 out << " () Bool)\n";
932 out << "(assert (= ";
933 convert_literal(l);
934 out << ' ';
935 convert_expr(prepared_expr);
936 out << "))\n";
937 }
938 else
939 {
940 auto identifier =
941 convert_identifier(std::string{"B"} + std::to_string(l.var_no()));
942 defined_expressions[expr] = identifier;
943 smt2_identifiers.insert(identifier);
944 out << "(define-fun " << identifier << " () Bool ";
945 convert_expr(prepared_expr);
946 out << ")\n";
947 }
948
949 return l;
950}
951
952exprt smt2_convt::handle(const exprt &expr)
953{
954 // We can only improve Booleans.
955 if(!expr.is_boolean())
956 return expr;
957
958 return literal_exprt(convert(expr));
959}
960
961void smt2_convt::convert_literal(const literalt l)
962{
963 if(l==const_literal(false))
964 out << "false";
965 else if(l==const_literal(true))
966 out << "true";
967 else
968 {
969 if(l.sign())
970 out << "(not ";
971
972 const auto identifier =
973 convert_identifier("B" + std::to_string(l.var_no()));
974
975 out << identifier;
976
977 if(l.sign())
978 out << ")";
979
980 smt2_identifiers.insert(identifier);
981 }
982}
983
984void smt2_convt::push()
985{
986 UNIMPLEMENTED;
987}
988
989void smt2_convt::push(const std::vector<exprt> &_assumptions)
990{
991 INVARIANT(assumptions.empty(), "nested contexts are not supported");
992
993 assumptions.reserve(_assumptions.size());
994 for(auto &assumption : _assumptions)
995 assumptions.push_back(convert(assumption));
996}
997
998void smt2_convt::pop()
999{
1000 assumptions.clear();
1001}
1002
1003static bool is_smt2_simple_identifier(const std::string &identifier)
1004{
1005 if(identifier.empty())
1006 return false;
1007
1008 if(isdigit(identifier[0]))
1009 return false;
1010
1011 for(auto ch : id2string(identifier))
1012 {
1013 if(!is_smt2_simple_symbol_character(ch))
1014 return false;
1015 }
1016
1017 return true;
1018}
1019
1020std::string smt2_convt::convert_identifier(const irep_idt &identifier)
1021{
1022 // Is this a "simple identifier"?
1023 if(is_smt2_simple_identifier(id2string(identifier)))
1024 return id2string(identifier);
1025
1026 // Backslashes are disallowed in quoted symbols just for simplicity.
1027 // Otherwise, for Common Lisp compatibility they would have to be treated
1028 // as escaping symbols.
1029
1030 std::string result = "|";
1031
1032 for(auto ch : identifier)
1033 {
1034 switch(ch)
1035 {
1036 case '|':
1037 case '\\':
1038 case '&': // we use the & for escaping
1039 result+='&';
1040 result+=std::to_string(ch);
1041 result+=';';
1042 break;
1043
1044 case '$': // $ _is_ allowed
1045 default:
1046 result+=ch;
1047 }
1048 }
1049
1050 result += '|';
1051
1052 return result;
1053}
1054
1055std::string smt2_convt::type2id(const typet &type) const
1056{
1057 if(type.id()==ID_floatbv)
1058 {
1059 ieee_float_spect spec(to_floatbv_type(type));
1060 return "f"+std::to_string(spec.width())+"_"+std::to_string(spec.f);
1061 }
1062 else if(type.id() == ID_bv)
1063 {
1064 return "B" + std::to_string(to_bitvector_type(type).get_width());
1065 }
1066 else if(type.id()==ID_unsignedbv)
1067 {
1068 return "u"+std::to_string(to_unsignedbv_type(type).get_width());
1069 }
1070 else if(type.id()==ID_c_bool)
1071 {
1072 return "u"+std::to_string(to_c_bool_type(type).get_width());
1073 }
1074 else if(type.id()==ID_signedbv)
1075 {
1076 return "s"+std::to_string(to_signedbv_type(type).get_width());
1077 }
1078 else if(type.id()==ID_bool)
1079 {
1080 return "b";
1081 }
1082 else if(type.id()==ID_c_enum_tag)
1083 {
1084 return type2id(ns.follow_tag(to_c_enum_tag_type(type)).underlying_type());
1085 }
1086 else if(type.id() == ID_pointer)
1087 {
1088 return "p" + std::to_string(to_pointer_type(type).get_width());
1089 }
1090 else if(type.id() == ID_struct_tag)
1091 {
1092 if(use_datatypes)
1093 return datatype_map.at(type);
1094 else
1095 return "S" + std::to_string(boolbv_width(type));
1096 }
1097 else if(type.id() == ID_union_tag)
1098 {
1099 return "U" + std::to_string(boolbv_width(type));
1100 }
1101 else if(type.id() == ID_array)
1102 {
1103 return "A" + type2id(to_array_type(type).element_type());
1104 }
1105 else
1106 {
1107 UNREACHABLE;
1108 }
1109}
1110
1111std::string smt2_convt::floatbv_suffix(const exprt &expr) const
1112{
1113 PRECONDITION(!expr.operands().empty());
1114 return "_" + type2id(to_multi_ary_expr(expr).op0().type()) + "->" +
1115 type2id(expr.type());
1116}
1117
1118void smt2_convt::convert_floatbv(const exprt &expr)
1119{
1120 PRECONDITION(!use_FPA_theory);
1121
1122 if(expr.id()==ID_symbol)
1123 {
1124 const irep_idt &id = to_symbol_expr(expr).get_identifier();
1125 out << convert_identifier(id);
1126 return;
1127 }
1128
1129 if(expr.id()==ID_smt2_symbol)
1130 {
1131 const irep_idt &id = to_smt2_symbol(expr).get_identifier();
1132 out << id;
1133 return;
1134 }
1135
1136 INVARIANT(
1137 !expr.operands().empty(), "non-symbol expressions shall have operands");
1138
1139 out << '('
1140 << convert_identifier(
1141 "float_bv." + expr.id_string() + floatbv_suffix(expr));
1142
1143 for(const auto &op : expr.operands())
1144 {
1145 out << ' ';
1146 convert_expr(op);
1147 }
1148
1149 out << ')';
1150}
1151
1152void smt2_convt::convert_string_literal(const std::string &s)
1153{
1154 out << '"';
1155 for(auto ch : s)
1156 {
1157 // " is escaped by double-quoting
1158 if(ch == '"')
1159 out << '"';
1160 out << ch;
1161 }
1162 out << '"';
1163}
1164
1165void smt2_convt::convert_expr(const exprt &expr)
1166{
1167 // try hash table first
1168 auto converter_result = converters.find(expr.id());
1169 if(converter_result != converters.end())
1170 {
1171 converter_result->second(expr);
1172 return; // done
1173 }
1174
1175 // huge monster case split over expression id
1176 if(expr.id()==ID_symbol)
1177 {
1178 const irep_idt &id = to_symbol_expr(expr).get_identifier();
1179 DATA_INVARIANT(!id.empty(), "symbol must have identifier");
1180 out << convert_identifier(id);
1181 }
1182 else if(expr.id()==ID_nondet_symbol)
1183 {
1184 const irep_idt &id = to_nondet_symbol_expr(expr).get_identifier();
1185 DATA_INVARIANT(!id.empty(), "nondet symbol must have identifier");
1186 out << convert_identifier("nondet_" + id2string(id));
1187 }
1188 else if(expr.id()==ID_smt2_symbol)
1189 {
1190 const irep_idt &id = to_smt2_symbol(expr).get_identifier();
1191 DATA_INVARIANT(!id.empty(), "smt2 symbol must have identifier");
1192 out << id;
1193 }
1194 else if(expr.id()==ID_typecast)
1195 {
1196 convert_typecast(to_typecast_expr(expr));
1197 }
1198 else if(expr.id()==ID_floatbv_typecast)
1199 {
1200 convert_floatbv_typecast(to_floatbv_typecast_expr(expr));
1201 }
1202 else if(expr.id()==ID_struct)
1203 {
1204 convert_struct(to_struct_expr(expr));
1205 }
1206 else if(expr.id()==ID_union)
1207 {
1208 convert_union(to_union_expr(expr));
1209 }
1210 else if(expr.is_constant())
1211 {
1212 convert_constant(to_constant_expr(expr));
1213 }
1214 else if(expr.id() == ID_concatenation && expr.operands().size() == 1)
1215 {
1216 DATA_INVARIANT_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(
1217 expr.type() == expr.operands().front().type(),
1218 "concatenation over a single operand should have matching types",
1219 expr.pretty());
1220
1221 convert_expr(expr.operands().front());
1222 }
1223 else if(
1224 expr.id() == ID_concatenation || expr.id() == ID_bitand ||
1225 expr.id() == ID_bitor || expr.id() == ID_bitxor)
1226 {
1227 DATA_INVARIANT_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(
1228 expr.operands().size() >= 2,
1229 "given expression should have at least two operands",
1230 expr.id_string());
1231
1232 out << "(";
1233
1234 if(expr.id()==ID_concatenation)
1235 out << "concat";
1236 else if(expr.id()==ID_bitand)
1237 out << "bvand";
1238 else if(expr.id()==ID_bitor)
1239 out << "bvor";
1240 else if(expr.id()==ID_bitxor)
1241 out << "bvxor";
1242 else if(expr.id()==ID_bitnand)
1243 out << "bvnand";
1244 else if(expr.id()==ID_bitnor)
1245 out << "bvnor";
1246
1247 for(const auto &op : expr.operands())
1248 {
1249 out << " ";
1250 flatten2bv(op);
1251 }
1252
1253 out << ")";
1254 }
1255 else if(
1256 expr.id() == ID_bitxnor || expr.id() == ID_bitnand ||
1257 expr.id() == ID_bitnor)
1258 {
1259 // SMT-LIB only has these as a binary expression,
1260 // owing to their ambiguity.
1261 if(expr.operands().size() == 2)
1262 {
1263 const auto &binary_expr = to_binary_expr(expr);
1264
1265 out << '(';
1266 if(binary_expr.id() == ID_bitxnor)
1267 out << "bvxnor";
1268 else if(binary_expr.id() == ID_bitnand)
1269 out << "bvnand";
1270 else if(binary_expr.id() == ID_bitnor)
1271 out << "bvnor";
1272 out << ' ';
1273 flatten2bv(binary_expr.op0());
1274 out << ' ';
1275 flatten2bv(binary_expr.op1());
1276 out << ')';
1277 }
1278 else if(expr.operands().size() == 1)
1279 {
1280 out << "(bvnot ";
1281 flatten2bv(to_unary_expr(expr).op());
1282 out << ')';
1283 }
1284 else if(expr.operands().size() >= 3)
1285 {
1286 out << "(bvnot (";
1287 if(expr.id() == ID_bitxnor)
1288 out << "bvxor";
1289 else if(expr.id() == ID_bitnand)
1290 out << "bvand";
1291 else if(expr.id() == ID_bitnor)
1292 out << "bvor";
1293
1294 for(const auto &op : expr.operands())
1295 {
1296 out << ' ';
1297 flatten2bv(op);
1298 }
1299
1300 out << "))"; // bvX, bvnot
1301 }
1302 else
1303 {
1304 DATA_INVARIANT(
1305 expr.operands().size() >= 1,
1306 expr.id_string() + " should have at least one operand");
1307 }
1308 }
1309 else if(expr.id()==ID_bitnot)
1310 {
1311 const bitnot_exprt &bitnot_expr = to_bitnot_expr(expr);
1312
1313 out << "(bvnot ";
1314 convert_expr(bitnot_expr.op());
1315 out << ")";
1316 }
1317 else if(expr.id()==ID_unary_minus)
1318 {
1319 const unary_minus_exprt &unary_minus_expr = to_unary_minus_expr(expr);
1320
1321 if(
1322 unary_minus_expr.type().id() == ID_rational ||
1323 unary_minus_expr.type().id() == ID_integer ||
1324 unary_minus_expr.type().id() == ID_real)
1325 {
1326 out << "(- ";
1327 convert_expr(unary_minus_expr.op());
1328 out << ")";
1329 }
1330 else if(unary_minus_expr.type().id() == ID_floatbv)
1331 {
1332 // this has no rounding mode
1333 if(use_FPA_theory)
1334 {
1335 out << "(fp.neg ";
1336 convert_expr(unary_minus_expr.op());
1337 out << ")";
1338 }
1339 else
1340 convert_floatbv(unary_minus_expr);
1341 }
1342 else
1343 {
1344 out << "(bvneg ";
1345 convert_expr(unary_minus_expr.op());
1346 out << ")";
1347 }
1348 }
1349 else if(expr.id()==ID_unary_plus)
1350 {
1351 // A no-op (apart from type promotion)
1352 convert_expr(to_unary_plus_expr(expr).op());
1353 }
1354 else if(expr.id()==ID_sign)
1355 {
1356 const sign_exprt &sign_expr = to_sign_expr(expr);
1357
1358 const typet &op_type = sign_expr.op().type();
1359
1360 if(op_type.id()==ID_floatbv)
1361 {
1362 if(use_FPA_theory)
1363 {
1364 out << "(fp.isNegative ";
1365 convert_expr(sign_expr.op());
1366 out << ")";
1367 }
1368 else
1369 convert_floatbv(sign_expr);
1370 }
1371 else if(op_type.id()==ID_signedbv)
1372 {
1373 std::size_t op_width=to_signedbv_type(op_type).get_width();
1374
1375 out << "(bvslt ";
1376 convert_expr(sign_expr.op());
1377 out << " (_ bv0 " << op_width << "))";
1378 }
1379 else
1380 INVARIANT_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(
1381 false,
1382 "sign should not be applied to unsupported type",
1383 sign_expr.type().id_string());
1384 }
1385 else if(expr.id()==ID_if)
1386 {
1387 const if_exprt &if_expr = to_if_expr(expr);
1388
1389 out << "(ite ";
1390 convert_expr(if_expr.cond());
1391 out << " ";
1392 convert_expr(if_expr.true_case());
1393 out << " ";
1394 convert_expr(if_expr.false_case());
1395 out << ")";
1396 }
1397 else if(expr.id()==ID_and ||
1398 expr.id()==ID_or ||
1399 expr.id()==ID_xor)
1400 {
1401 DATA_INVARIANT(
1402 expr.is_boolean(),
1403 "logical and, or, and xor expressions should have Boolean type");
1404 DATA_INVARIANT(
1405 expr.operands().size() >= 2,
1406 "logical and, or, and xor expressions should have at least two operands");
1407
1408 out << "(" << expr.id();
1409 for(const auto &op : expr.operands())
1410 {
1411 out << " ";
1412 convert_expr(op);
1413 }
1414 out << ")";
1415 }
1416 else if(expr.id() == ID_nand || expr.id() == ID_nor || expr.id() == ID_xnor)
1417 {
1418 DATA_INVARIANT(
1419 expr.is_boolean(),
1420 "logical nand, nor, xnor expressions should have Boolean type");
1421 DATA_INVARIANT(
1422 expr.operands().size() >= 1,
1423 "logical nand, nor, xnor expressions should have at least one operand");
1424
1425 // SMT-LIB doesn't have nand, nor, xnor
1426 out << "(not ";
1427 if(expr.operands().size() == 1)
1428 convert_expr(to_multi_ary_expr(expr).op0());
1429 else
1430 {
1431 if(expr.id() == ID_nand)
1432 out << "(and";
1433 else if(expr.id() == ID_nor)
1434 out << "(and";
1435 else if(expr.id() == ID_xnor)
1436 out << "(xor";
1437 else
1438 DATA_INVARIANT(false, "unexpected expression");
1439 for(const auto &op : expr.operands())
1440 {
1441 out << ' ';
1442 convert_expr(op);
1443 }
1444 out << ')'; // or, and, xor
1445 }
1446 out << ')'; // not
1447 }
1448 else if(expr.id()==ID_implies)
1449 {
1450 const implies_exprt &implies_expr = to_implies_expr(expr);
1451
1452 DATA_INVARIANT(

1457 out << " ";

1459 out << ")";

1488 out << " ";

1654 type.id()==ID_signedbv ||
1655 type.id()==ID_bv)

1670 // the value that is shifted -- odd!
1671

1673 if(distance_type.id() == ID_integer || distance_type.id() == ID_natural)

1675 const mp_integer i =
1676 numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(to_constant_expr(shift_expr.distance()));

1681 convert_expr(tmp);
1682 }

1684 distance_type.id() == ID_signedbv ||
1685 distance_type.id() == ID_unsignedbv ||

1692 convert_expr(shift_expr.distance());

1695 out << "((_ zero_extend " << width_op0-width_op1 << ") ";
1696 convert_expr(shift_expr.distance());
1697 out << ")"; // zero_extend
1698 }
1699 else // width_op0<width_op1
1700 {
1701 out << "((_ extract " << width_op0-1 << " 0) ";
1702 convert_expr(shift_expr.distance());
1703 out << ")"; // extract
1704 }
1705 }

1709 "unsupported distance type for " + shift_expr.id_string() + ": " +
1710 distance_type.id_string());
1711 }
1712
1713 out << ")"; // bv*sh
1714 }

1716 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
1717 "unsupported type for " + shift_expr.id_string() + ": " +
1718 type.id_string());
1719 }

1726 type.id() == ID_unsignedbv || type.id() == ID_signedbv ||
1727 type.id() == ID_bv)

1732 out << "((_ rotate_left";
1733 else if(shift_expr.id() == ID_ror)
1734 out << "((_ rotate_right";
1735 else

1737
1738 out << ' ';

1741

1743 {
1744 out << distance_int_op.value();
1745 }

1747 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
1748 "distance type for " + shift_expr.id_string() + "must be constant");
1749
1750 out << ") ";
1751 convert_expr(shift_expr.op());
1752
1753 out << ")"; // rotate_*
1754 }

1756 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
1757 "unsupported type for " + shift_expr.id_string() + ": " +
1758 type.id_string());
1759 }

1761 {

1767 }

1771 }

1775 }

1800

2129 const auto &op1 = to_binary_expr(expr).op1();
2130
2131 DATA_INVARIANT(
2132 keep_result || expr.is_boolean(),
2133 "overflow plus and overflow minus expressions shall be of Boolean type");
2134
2135 bool subtract = can_cast_expr<minus_overflow_exprt>(expr) ||
2136 expr.id() == ID_overflow_result_minus;
2137 const typet &op_type = op0.type();
2138 std::size_t width=boolbv_width(op_type);

2140 if(op_type.id()==ID_signedbv)
2141 {
2142 // an overflow occurs if the top two bits of the extended sum differ

2147 out << ")";
2148 out << " ((_ sign_extend 1) ";
2149 convert_expr(op1);
2150 out << ")))) "; // sign_extend, bvadd/sub
2151 if(keep_result)
2152 {
2153 if(use_datatypes)
2154 {
2155 const std::string &smt_typename = datatype_map.at(expr.type());
2156
2157 // use the constructor for the Z3 datatype
2158 out << "(mk-" << smt_typename;
2159 }
2160 else
2161 out << "(concat";
2162
2163 out << " ((_ extract " << width - 1 << " 0) ?sum) ";
2164 if(!use_datatypes)
2165 out << "(ite ";
2166 }
2167 out << "(not (= "
2168 "((_ extract " << width << " " << width << ") ?sum) "
2169 "((_ extract " << (width-1) << " " << (width-1) << ") ?sum)";
2170 out << "))"; // =, not
2171 if(keep_result)
2172 {
2173 if(!use_datatypes)
2174 out << " #b1 #b0)";
2175 out << ")"; // concat
2176 }
2177 out << ")"; // let
2178 }
2179 else if(op_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv ||
2180 op_type.id()==ID_pointer)
2181 {
2182 // overflow is simply carry-out
2183 out << "(let ((?sum (" << (subtract ? "bvsub" : "bvadd");
2184 out << " ((_ zero_extend 1) ";
2185 convert_expr(op0);
2186 out << ")";
2187 out << " ((_ zero_extend 1) ";
2188 convert_expr(op1);
2189 out << "))))"; // zero_extend, bvsub/bvadd
2190 if(keep_result && !use_datatypes)
2191 out << " ?sum";
2192 else
2193 {
2194 if(keep_result && use_datatypes)
2195 {
2196 const std::string &smt_typename = datatype_map.at(expr.type());
2197
2198 // use the constructor for the Z3 datatype
2199 out << "(mk-" << smt_typename;
2200 out << " ((_ extract " << width - 1 << " 0) ?sum) ";
2201 }
2202
2203 out << "(= ";
2204 out << "((_ extract " << width << " " << width << ") ?sum)";
2205 out << "#b1)"; // =
2206
2207 if(keep_result && use_datatypes)
2208 out << ")"; // mk
2209 }
2210 out << ")"; // let
2211 }
2212 else
2213 INVARIANT_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(
2214 false,
2215 "overflow check should not be performed on unsupported type",
2216 op_type.id_string());
2217 }
2218 else if(
2219 can_cast_expr<mult_overflow_exprt>(expr) ||
2220 expr.id() == ID_overflow_result_mult)
2221 {
2222 const bool keep_result = can_cast_expr<overflow_result_exprt>(expr);
2223
2224 const auto &op0 = to_binary_expr(expr).op0();
2225 const auto &op1 = to_binary_expr(expr).op1();
2226
2227 DATA_INVARIANT(
2228 keep_result || expr.is_boolean(),
2229 "overflow mult expression shall be of Boolean type");
2230
2231 // No better idea than to multiply with double the bits and then compare
2232 // with max value.
2233
2234 const typet &op_type = op0.type();
2235 std::size_t width=boolbv_width(op_type);
2236
2237 if(op_type.id()==ID_signedbv)
2238 {
2239 out << "(let ( (prod (bvmul ((_ sign_extend " << width << ") ";
2240 convert_expr(op0);
2241 out << ") ((_ sign_extend " << width << ") ";
2242 convert_expr(op1);
2243 out << ")) )) ";
2244 if(keep_result)
2245 {
2246 if(use_datatypes)
2247 {
2248 const std::string &smt_typename = datatype_map.at(expr.type());
2249
2250 // use the constructor for the Z3 datatype
2251 out << "(mk-" << smt_typename;
2252 }
2253 else
2254 out << "(concat";
2255
2256 out << " ((_ extract " << width - 1 << " 0) prod) ";
2257 if(!use_datatypes)
2258 out << "(ite ";
2259 }
2260 out << "(or (bvsge prod (_ bv" << power(2, width-1) << " "
2261 << width*2 << "))";
2262 out << " (bvslt prod (bvneg (_ bv" << power(2, width - 1) << " "
2263 << width * 2 << "))))";
2264 if(keep_result)
2265 {
2266 if(!use_datatypes)
2267 out << " #b1 #b0)";
2268 out << ")"; // concat
2269 }
2270 out << ")";
2271 }
2272 else if(op_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv)
2273 {
2274 out << "(let ((prod (bvmul ((_ zero_extend " << width << ") ";
2275 convert_expr(op0);
2276 out << ") ((_ zero_extend " << width << ") ";
2277 convert_expr(op1);
2278 out << ")))) ";
2279 if(keep_result)
2280 {
2281 if(use_datatypes)
2282 {
2283 const std::string &smt_typename = datatype_map.at(expr.type());
2284
2285 // use the constructor for the Z3 datatype
2286 out << "(mk-" << smt_typename;
2287 }
2288 else
2289 out << "(concat";
2290
2291 out << " ((_ extract " << width - 1 << " 0) prod) ";
2292 if(!use_datatypes)
2293 out << "(ite ";
2294 }
2295 out << "(bvuge prod (_ bv" << power(2, width) << " " << width * 2 << "))";
2296 if(keep_result)
2297 {
2298 if(!use_datatypes)
2299 out << " #b1 #b0)";
2300 out << ")"; // concat
2301 }
2302 out << ")";
2303 }
2304 else
2305 INVARIANT_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(
2306 false,
2307 "overflow check should not be performed on unsupported type",
2308 op_type.id_string());
2309 }
2310 else if(expr.id() == ID_saturating_plus || expr.id() == ID_saturating_minus)
2311 {
2312 const bool subtract = expr.id() == ID_saturating_minus;
2313 const auto &op_type = expr.type();
2314 const auto &op0 = to_binary_expr(expr).op0();
2315 const auto &op1 = to_binary_expr(expr).op1();
2316
2317 if(op_type.id() == ID_signedbv)
2318 {
2319 auto width = to_signedbv_type(op_type).get_width();
2320
2321 // compute sum with one extra bit
2322 out << "(let ((?sum (";
2323 out << (subtract ? "bvsub" : "bvadd");
2324 out << " ((_ sign_extend 1) ";
2325 convert_expr(op0);
2326 out << ")";
2327 out << " ((_ sign_extend 1) ";
2328 convert_expr(op1);
2329 out << ")))) "; // sign_extend, bvadd/sub
2330
2331 // pick one of MAX, MIN, or the sum
2332 out << "(ite (= "
2333 "((_ extract "
2334 << width << " " << width
2335 << ") ?sum) "
2336 "((_ extract "
2337 << (width - 1) << " " << (width - 1) << ") ?sum)";
2338 out << ") "; // =
2339
2340 // no overflow and no underflow case, return the sum
2341 out << "((_ extract " << width - 1 << " 0) ?sum) ";
2342
2343 // MAX
2344 out << "(ite (= ((_ extract " << width << " " << width << ") ?sum) #b0) ";
2345 convert_expr(to_signedbv_type(op_type).largest_expr());
2346
2347 // MIN
2348 convert_expr(to_signedbv_type(op_type).smallest_expr());
2349 out << ")))"; // ite, ite, let
2350 }
2351 else if(op_type.id() == ID_unsignedbv)
2352 {
2353 auto width = to_unsignedbv_type(op_type).get_width();
2354
2355 // compute sum with one extra bit
2356 out << "(let ((?sum (" << (subtract ? "bvsub" : "bvadd");
2357 out << " ((_ zero_extend 1) ";
2358 convert_expr(op0);
2359 out << ")";
2360 out << " ((_ zero_extend 1) ";
2361 convert_expr(op1);
2362 out << "))))"; // zero_extend, bvsub/bvadd
2363
2364 // pick one of MAX, MIN, or the sum
2365 out << "(ite (= ((_ extract " << width << " " << width << ") ?sum) #b0) ";
2366
2367 // no overflow and no underflow case, return the sum
2368 out << " ((_ extract " << width - 1 << " 0) ?sum) ";
2369
2370 // overflow when adding, underflow when subtracting
2371 if(subtract)
2372 convert_expr(to_unsignedbv_type(op_type).smallest_expr());
2373 else
2374 convert_expr(to_unsignedbv_type(op_type).largest_expr());
2375
2376 // MIN
2377 out << "))"; // ite, let
2378 }
2379 else
2380 INVARIANT_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(
2381 false,
2382 "saturating_plus/minus on unsupported type",
2383 op_type.id_string());
2384 }
2385 else if(expr.id()==ID_array)
2386 {
2387 defined_expressionst::const_iterator it=defined_expressions.find(expr);
2388 CHECK_RETURN(it != defined_expressions.end());
2389 out << it->second;
2390 }
2391 else if(expr.id()==ID_literal)
2392 {
2393 convert_literal(to_literal_expr(expr).get_literal());
2394 }
2395 else if(expr.id()==ID_forall ||
2396 expr.id()==ID_exists)
2397 {
2398 const quantifier_exprt &quantifier_expr = to_quantifier_expr(expr);
2399
2400 if(solver==solvert::MATHSAT)
2401 // NOLINTNEXTLINE(readability/throw)
2402 throw "MathSAT does not support quantifiers";
2403
2404 if(quantifier_expr.id() == ID_forall)
2405 out << "(forall ";
2406 else if(quantifier_expr.id() == ID_exists)
2407 out << "(exists ";
2408
2409 out << '(';
2410 bool first = true;
2411 for(const auto &bound : quantifier_expr.variables())
2412 {
2413 if(first)
2414 first = false;
2415 else
2416 out << ' ';
2417 out << '(';
2418 convert_expr(bound);
2419 out << ' ';
2420 convert_type(bound.type());
2421 out << ')';
2422 }
2423 out << ") ";
2424
2425 convert_expr(quantifier_expr.where());
2426
2427 out << ')';
2428 }
2429 else if(
2430 const auto object_size = expr_try_dynamic_cast<object_size_exprt>(expr))
2431 {
2432 out << object_sizes[*object_size];
2433 }
2434 else if(expr.id()==ID_let)
2435 {
2436 const let_exprt &let_expr=to_let_expr(expr);
2437 const auto &variables = let_expr.variables();
2438 const auto &values = let_expr.values();
2439
2440 out << "(let (";
2441 bool first = true;
2442
2443 for(auto &binding : make_range(variables).zip(values))
2444 {
2445 if(first)
2446 first = false;
2447 else
2448 out << ' ';
2449
2450 out << '(';
2451 convert_expr(binding.first);
2452 out << ' ';
2453 convert_expr(binding.second);
2454 out << ')';
2455 }
2456
2457 out << ") "; // bindings
2458
2459 convert_expr(let_expr.where());
2460 out << ')'; // let
2461 }
2462 else if(expr.id()==ID_constraint_select_one)
2463 {
2464 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
2465 "smt2_convt::convert_expr: '" + expr.id_string() +
2466 "' is not yet supported");
2467 }
2468 else if(expr.id() == ID_bswap)
2469 {
2470 const bswap_exprt &bswap_expr = to_bswap_expr(expr);
2471
2472 DATA_INVARIANT(
2473 bswap_expr.op().type() == bswap_expr.type(),
2474 "operand of byte swap expression shall have same type as the expression");
2475
2476 // first 'let' the operand
2477 out << "(let ((bswap_op ";
2478 convert_expr(bswap_expr.op());
2479 out << ")) ";
2480
2481 if(
2482 bswap_expr.type().id() == ID_signedbv ||
2483 bswap_expr.type().id() == ID_unsignedbv)
2484 {
2485 const std::size_t width =
2486 to_bitvector_type(bswap_expr.type()).get_width();
2487
2488 const std::size_t bits_per_byte = bswap_expr.get_bits_per_byte();
2489
2490 // width must be multiple of bytes
2491 DATA_INVARIANT(
2492 width % bits_per_byte == 0,
2493 "bit width indicated by type of bswap expression should be a multiple "
2494 "of the number of bits per byte");
2495
2496 const std::size_t bytes = width / bits_per_byte;
2497
2498 if(bytes <= 1)
2499 out << "bswap_op";
2500 else
2501 {
2502 // do a parallel 'let' for each byte
2503 out << "(let (";
2504
2505 for(std::size_t byte = 0; byte < bytes; byte++)
2506 {
2507 if(byte != 0)
2508 out << ' ';
2509 out << "(bswap_byte_" << byte << ' ';
2510 out << "((_ extract " << (byte * bits_per_byte + (bits_per_byte - 1))
2511 << " " << (byte * bits_per_byte) << ") bswap_op)";
2512 out << ')';
2513 }
2514
2515 out << ") ";
2516
2517 // now stitch back together with 'concat'
2518 out << "(concat";
2519
2520 for(std::size_t byte = 0; byte < bytes; byte++)
2521 out << " bswap_byte_" << byte;
2522
2523 out << ')'; // concat
2524 out << ')'; // let bswap_byte_*
2525 }
2526 }
2527 else
2528 UNEXPECTEDCASE("bswap must get bitvector operand");
2529
2530 out << ')'; // let bswap_op
2531 }
2532 else if(expr.id() == ID_popcount)
2533 {
2534 convert_expr(simplify_expr(to_popcount_expr(expr).lower(), ns));
2535 }
2536 else if(expr.id() == ID_count_leading_zeros)
2537 {
2538 convert_expr(simplify_expr(to_count_leading_zeros_expr(expr).lower(), ns));
2539 }
2540 else if(expr.id() == ID_count_trailing_zeros)
2541 {
2542 convert_expr(simplify_expr(to_count_trailing_zeros_expr(expr).lower(), ns));
2543 }
2544 else if(expr.id() == ID_find_first_set)
2545 {
2546 convert_expr(simplify_expr(to_find_first_set_expr(expr).lower(), ns));
2547 }
2548 else if(expr.id() == ID_bitreverse)
2549 {
2550 convert_expr(simplify_expr(to_bitreverse_expr(expr).lower(), ns));
2551 }
2552 else if(expr.id() == ID_zero_extend)
2553 {
2554 convert_expr(to_zero_extend_expr(expr).lower());
2555 }
2556 else if(expr.id() == ID_function_application)
2557 {
2558 const auto &function_application_expr = to_function_application_expr(expr);
2559 // do not use parentheses if there function is a constant
2560 if(function_application_expr.arguments().empty())
2561 {
2562 convert_expr(function_application_expr.function());
2563 }
2564 else
2565 {
2566 out << '(';
2567 convert_expr(function_application_expr.function());
2568 for(auto &op : function_application_expr.arguments())
2569 {
2570 out << ' ';
2571 convert_expr(op);
2572 }
2573 out << ')';
2574 }
2575 }
2576 else if(expr.id() == ID_cond)
2577 {
2578 // use the lowering
2579 convert_expr(to_cond_expr(expr).lower());
2580 }
2581 else
2582 INVARIANT_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(
2583 false,
2584 "smt2_convt::convert_expr should not be applied to unsupported "
2585 "expression",
2586 expr.id_string());
2587}
2588
2589void smt2_convt::convert_typecast(const typecast_exprt &expr)
2590{
2591 const exprt &src = expr.op();
2592
2593 typet dest_type = expr.type();
2594 if(dest_type.id()==ID_c_enum_tag)
2595 dest_type=ns.follow_tag(to_c_enum_tag_type(dest_type));
2596
2597 typet src_type = src.type();
2598 if(src_type.id()==ID_c_enum_tag)
2599 src_type=ns.follow_tag(to_c_enum_tag_type(src_type));
2600
2601 if(dest_type.id()==ID_bool)
2602 {
2603 // this is comparison with zero
2604 if(src_type.id()==ID_signedbv ||
2605 src_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv ||
2606 src_type.id()==ID_c_bool ||
2607 src_type.id()==ID_fixedbv ||
2608 src_type.id()==ID_pointer ||
2609 src_type.id()==ID_integer)
2610 {
2611 out << "(not (= ";
2612 convert_expr(src);
2613 out << " ";
2614 convert_expr(from_integer(0, src_type));
2615 out << "))";
2616 }
2617 else if(src_type.id()==ID_floatbv)
2618 {
2619 if(use_FPA_theory)
2620 {
2621 out << "(not (fp.isZero ";
2622 convert_expr(src);
2623 out << "))";
2624 }
2625 else
2626 convert_floatbv(expr);
2627 }
2628 else
2629 {
2630 UNEXPECTEDCASE("TODO typecast1 "+src_type.id_string()+" -> bool");
2631 }
2632 }
2633 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_c_bool)
2634 {
2635 std::size_t to_width=boolbv_width(dest_type);
2636 out << "(ite ";
2637 out << "(not (= ";
2638 convert_expr(src);
2639 out << " ";
2640 convert_expr(from_integer(0, src_type));
2641 out << "))"; // not, =
2642 out << " (_ bv1 " << to_width << ")";
2643 out << " (_ bv0 " << to_width << ")";
2644 out << ")"; // ite
2645 }
2646 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_signedbv ||
2647 dest_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv ||
2648 dest_type.id()==ID_c_enum ||
2649 dest_type.id()==ID_bv)
2650 {
2651 std::size_t to_width=boolbv_width(dest_type);
2652
2653 if(src_type.id()==ID_signedbv || // from signedbv
2654 src_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv || // from unsigedbv
2655 src_type.id()==ID_c_bool ||
2656 src_type.id()==ID_c_enum ||
2657 src_type.id()==ID_bv)
2658 {
2659 std::size_t from_width=boolbv_width(src_type);
2660
2661 if(from_width==to_width)
2662 convert_expr(src); // ignore
2663 else if(from_width<to_width) // extend
2664 {
2665 if(src_type.id()==ID_signedbv)
2666 out << "((_ sign_extend ";
2667 else
2668 out << "((_ zero_extend ";
2669
2670 out << (to_width-from_width)
2671 << ") "; // ind
2672 convert_expr(src);
2673 out << ")";
2674 }
2675 else // chop off extra bits
2676 {
2677 out << "((_ extract " << (to_width-1) << " 0) ";
2678 convert_expr(src);
2679 out << ")";
2680 }
2681 }
2682 else if(src_type.id()==ID_fixedbv) // from fixedbv to int
2683 {
2684 const fixedbv_typet &fixedbv_type=to_fixedbv_type(src_type);
2685
2686 std::size_t from_width=fixedbv_type.get_width();
2687 std::size_t from_integer_bits=fixedbv_type.get_integer_bits();
2688 std::size_t from_fraction_bits=fixedbv_type.get_fraction_bits();
2689
2690 // we might need to round up in case of negative numbers
2691 // e.g., (int)(-1.00001)==1
2692
2693 out << "(let ((?tcop ";
2694 convert_expr(src);
2695 out << ")) ";
2696
2697 out << "(bvadd ";
2698
2699 if(to_width>from_integer_bits)
2700 {
2701 out << "((_ sign_extend "
2702 << (to_width-from_integer_bits) << ") ";
2703 out << "((_ extract " << (from_width-1) << " "
2704 << from_fraction_bits << ") ";
2705 convert_expr(src);
2706 out << "))";
2707 }
2708 else
2709 {
2710 out << "((_ extract " << (from_fraction_bits+to_width-1)
2711 << " " << from_fraction_bits << ") ";
2712 convert_expr(src);
2713 out << ")";
2714 }
2715
2716 out << " (ite (and ";
2717
2718 // some fraction bit is not zero
2719 out << "(not (= ((_ extract " << (from_fraction_bits-1) << " 0) ?tcop) "
2720 "(_ bv0 " << from_fraction_bits << ")))";
2721
2722 // number negative
2723 out << " (= ((_ extract " << (from_width-1) << " " << (from_width-1)
2724 << ") ?tcop) #b1)";
2725
2726 out << ")"; // and
2727
2728 out << " (_ bv1 " << to_width << ") (_ bv0 " << to_width << "))"; // ite
2729 out << ")"; // bvadd
2730 out << ")"; // let
2731 }
2732 else if(src_type.id()==ID_floatbv) // from floatbv to int
2733 {
2734 if(dest_type.id()==ID_bv)
2735 {
2736 // this is _NOT_ a semantic conversion, but bit-wise
2737
2738 if(use_FPA_theory)
2739 {
2740 defined_expressionst::const_iterator it =
2741 defined_expressions.find(expr);
2742 CHECK_RETURN(it != defined_expressions.end());
2743 out << it->second;
2744 }
2745 else
2746 {
2747 // straight-forward if width matches
2748 convert_expr(src);
2749 }
2750 }
2751 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_signedbv)
2752 {
2753 // this should be floatbv_typecast, not typecast
2754 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
2755 "typecast unexpected "+src_type.id_string()+" -> "+
2756 dest_type.id_string());
2757 }
2758 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv)
2759 {
2760 // this should be floatbv_typecast, not typecast
2761 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
2762 "typecast unexpected "+src_type.id_string()+" -> "+
2763 dest_type.id_string());
2764 }
2765 }
2766 else if(src_type.id()==ID_bool) // from boolean to int
2767 {
2768 out << "(ite ";
2769 convert_expr(src);
2770
2771 if(dest_type.id()==ID_fixedbv)
2772 {
2773 fixedbv_spect spec(to_fixedbv_type(dest_type));
2774 out << " (concat (_ bv1 "
2775 << spec.integer_bits << ") " <<
2776 "(_ bv0 " << spec.get_fraction_bits() << ")) " <<
2777 "(_ bv0 " << spec.width << ")";
2778 }
2779 else
2780 {
2781 out << " (_ bv1 " << to_width << ")";
2782 out << " (_ bv0 " << to_width << ")";
2783 }
2784
2785 out << ")";
2786 }
2787 else if(src_type.id()==ID_pointer) // from pointer to int
2788 {
2789 std::size_t from_width=boolbv_width(src_type);
2790
2791 if(from_width<to_width) // extend
2792 {
2793 out << "((_ sign_extend ";
2794 out << (to_width-from_width)
2795 << ") ";
2796 convert_expr(src);
2797 out << ")";
2798 }
2799 else // chop off extra bits
2800 {
2801 out << "((_ extract " << (to_width-1) << " 0) ";
2802 convert_expr(src);
2803 out << ")";
2804 }
2805 }
2806 else if(src_type.id()==ID_integer) // from integer to bit-vector
2807 {
2808 // must be constant
2809 if(src.is_constant())
2810 {
2811 mp_integer i = numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(to_constant_expr(src));
2812 out << "(_ bv" << i << " " << to_width << ")";
2813 }
2814 else
2815 SMT2_TODO("can't convert non-constant integer to bitvector");
2816 }
2817 else if(
2818 src_type.id() == ID_struct ||
2819 src_type.id() == ID_struct_tag) // flatten a struct to a bit-vector
2820 {
2821 if(use_datatypes)
2822 {
2823 INVARIANT(
2824 boolbv_width(src_type) == boolbv_width(dest_type),
2825 "bit vector with of source and destination type shall be equal");
2826 flatten2bv(src);
2827 }
2828 else
2829 {
2830 INVARIANT(
2831 boolbv_width(src_type) == boolbv_width(dest_type),
2832 "bit vector with of source and destination type shall be equal");
2833 convert_expr(src); // nothing else to do!
2834 }
2835 }
2836 else if(
2837 src_type.id() == ID_union ||
2838 src_type.id() == ID_union_tag) // flatten a union
2839 {
2840 INVARIANT(
2841 boolbv_width(src_type) == boolbv_width(dest_type),
2842 "bit vector with of source and destination type shall be equal");
2843 convert_expr(src); // nothing else to do!
2844 }
2845 else if(src_type.id()==ID_c_bit_field)
2846 {
2847 std::size_t from_width=boolbv_width(src_type);
2848
2849 if(from_width==to_width)
2850 convert_expr(src); // ignore
2851 else
2852 {
2853 typet t=c_bit_field_replacement_type(to_c_bit_field_type(src_type), ns);
2854 typecast_exprt tmp(typecast_exprt(src, t), dest_type);
2855 convert_typecast(tmp);
2856 }
2857 }
2858 else
2859 {
2860 std::ostringstream e_str;
2861 e_str << src_type.id() << " -> " << dest_type.id()
2862 << " src == " << format(src);
2863 UNEXPECTEDCASE("TODO typecast2 " + e_str.str());
2864 }
2865 }
2866 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_fixedbv) // to fixedbv
2867 {
2868 const fixedbv_typet &fixedbv_type=to_fixedbv_type(dest_type);
2869 std::size_t to_fraction_bits=fixedbv_type.get_fraction_bits();
2870 std::size_t to_integer_bits=fixedbv_type.get_integer_bits();
2871
2872 if(src_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv ||
2873 src_type.id()==ID_signedbv ||
2874 src_type.id()==ID_c_enum)
2875 {
2876 // integer to fixedbv
2877
2878 std::size_t from_width=to_bitvector_type(src_type).get_width();
2879 out << "(concat ";
2880
2881 if(from_width==to_integer_bits)
2882 convert_expr(src);
2883 else if(from_width>to_integer_bits)
2884 {
2885 // too many integer bits
2886 out << "((_ extract " << (to_integer_bits-1) << " 0) ";
2887 convert_expr(src);
2888 out << ")";
2889 }
2890 else
2891 {
2892 // too few integer bits
2893 INVARIANT(
2894 from_width < to_integer_bits,
2895 "from_width should be smaller than to_integer_bits as other case "
2896 "have been handled above");
2897 if(dest_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv)
2898 {
2899 out << "(_ zero_extend "
2900 << (to_integer_bits-from_width) << ") ";
2901 convert_expr(src);
2902 out << ")";
2903 }
2904 else
2905 {
2906 out << "((_ sign_extend "
2907 << (to_integer_bits-from_width) << ") ";
2908 convert_expr(src);
2909 out << ")";
2910 }
2911 }
2912
2913 out << "(_ bv0 " << to_fraction_bits << ")";
2914 out << ")"; // concat
2915 }
2916 else if(src_type.id()==ID_bool) // bool to fixedbv
2917 {
2918 out << "(concat (concat"
2919 << " (_ bv0 " << (to_integer_bits-1) << ") ";
2920 flatten2bv(src); // produces #b0 or #b1
2921 out << ") (_ bv0 "
2922 << to_fraction_bits
2923 << "))";
2924 }
2925 else if(src_type.id()==ID_fixedbv) // fixedbv to fixedbv
2926 {
2927 const fixedbv_typet &from_fixedbv_type=to_fixedbv_type(src_type);
2928 std::size_t from_fraction_bits=from_fixedbv_type.get_fraction_bits();
2929 std::size_t from_integer_bits=from_fixedbv_type.get_integer_bits();
2930 std::size_t from_width=from_fixedbv_type.get_width();
2931
2932 out << "(let ((?tcop ";
2933 convert_expr(src);
2934 out << ")) ";
2935
2936 out << "(concat ";
2937
2938 if(to_integer_bits<=from_integer_bits)
2939 {
2940 out << "((_ extract "
2941 << (from_fraction_bits+to_integer_bits-1) << " "
2942 << from_fraction_bits
2943 << ") ?tcop)";
2944 }
2945 else
2946 {
2947 INVARIANT(
2948 to_integer_bits > from_integer_bits,
2949 "to_integer_bits should be greater than from_integer_bits as the"
2950 "other case has been handled above");
2951 out << "((_ sign_extend "
2952 << (to_integer_bits-from_integer_bits)
2953 << ") ((_ extract "
2954 << (from_width-1) << " "
2955 << from_fraction_bits
2956 << ") ?tcop))";
2957 }
2958
2959 out << " ";
2960
2961 if(to_fraction_bits<=from_fraction_bits)
2962 {
2963 out << "((_ extract "
2964 << (from_fraction_bits-1) << " "
2965 << (from_fraction_bits-to_fraction_bits)
2966 << ") ?tcop)";
2967 }
2968 else
2969 {
2970 INVARIANT(
2971 to_fraction_bits > from_fraction_bits,
2972 "to_fraction_bits should be greater than from_fraction_bits as the"
2973 "other case has been handled above");
2974 out << "(concat ((_ extract "
2975 << (from_fraction_bits-1) << " 0) ";
2976 convert_expr(src);
2977 out << ")"
2978 << " (_ bv0 " << to_fraction_bits-from_fraction_bits
2979 << "))";
2980 }
2981
2982 out << "))"; // concat, let
2983 }
2984 else
2985 UNEXPECTEDCASE("unexpected typecast to fixedbv");
2986 }
2987 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_pointer)
2988 {
2989 std::size_t to_width=boolbv_width(dest_type);
2990
2991 if(src_type.id()==ID_pointer) // pointer to pointer
2992 {
2993 // this just passes through
2994 convert_expr(src);
2995 }
2996 else if(
2997 src_type.id() == ID_unsignedbv || src_type.id() == ID_signedbv ||
2998 src_type.id() == ID_bv)
2999 {
3000 // integer to pointer
3001
3002 std::size_t from_width=boolbv_width(src_type);
3003
3004 if(from_width==to_width)
3005 convert_expr(src);
3006 else if(from_width<to_width)
3007 {
3008 out << "((_ sign_extend "
3009 << (to_width-from_width)
3010 << ") ";
3011 convert_expr(src);
3012 out << ")"; // sign_extend
3013 }
3014 else // from_width>to_width
3015 {
3016 out << "((_ extract " << to_width << " 0) ";
3017 convert_expr(src);
3018 out << ")"; // extract
3019 }
3020 }
3021 else
3022 UNEXPECTEDCASE("TODO typecast3 "+src_type.id_string()+" -> pointer");
3023 }
3024 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_range)
3025 {
3026 auto &dest_range_type = to_range_type(dest_type);
3027 const auto dest_size =
3028 dest_range_type.get_to() - dest_range_type.get_from() + 1;
3029 const auto dest_width = address_bits(dest_size);
3030 if(src_type.id() == ID_range)
3031 {
3032 auto &src_range_type = to_range_type(src_type);
3033 const auto src_size =
3034 src_range_type.get_to() - src_range_type.get_from() + 1;
3035 const auto src_width = address_bits(src_size);
3036 if(src_width < dest_width)
3037 {
3038 out << "((_ zero_extend " << dest_width - src_width << ") ";
3039 convert_expr(src);
3040 out << ')'; // zero_extend
3041 }
3042 else if(src_width > dest_width)
3043 {
3044 out << "((_ extract " << dest_width - 1 << " 0) ";
3045 convert_expr(src);
3046 out << ')'; // extract
3047 }
3048 else // src_width == dest_width
3049 {
3050 convert_expr(src);
3051 }
3052 }
3053 else
3054 SMT2_TODO("typecast from " + src_type.id_string() + " to range");
3055 }
3056 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_floatbv)
3057 {
3058 // Typecast from integer to floating-point should have be been
3059 // converted to ID_floatbv_typecast during symbolic execution,
3060 // adding the rounding mode. See
3061 // smt2_convt::convert_floatbv_typecast.
3062 // The exception is bool and c_bool to float.
3063 const auto &dest_floatbv_type = to_floatbv_type(dest_type);
3064
3065 if(src_type.id()==ID_bool)
3066 {
3067 out << "(ite ";
3068 convert_expr(src);
3069 out << ' ';
3070 convert_constant(ieee_floatt::one(dest_floatbv_type).to_expr());
3071 out << ' ';
3072 convert_constant(ieee_floatt::zero(dest_floatbv_type).to_expr());
3073 out << ')';
3074 }
3075 else if(src_type.id()==ID_c_bool)
3076 {
3077 // turn into proper bool
3078 const typecast_exprt tmp(src, bool_typet());
3079 convert_typecast(typecast_exprt(tmp, dest_type));
3080 }
3081 else if(src_type.id() == ID_bv)
3082 {
3083 if(to_bv_type(src_type).get_width() != dest_floatbv_type.get_width())
3084 {
3085 UNEXPECTEDCASE("Typecast bv -> float with wrong width");
3086 }
3087
3088 if(use_FPA_theory)
3089 {
3090 out << "((_ to_fp " << dest_floatbv_type.get_e() << " "
3091 << dest_floatbv_type.get_f() + 1 << ") ";
3092 convert_expr(src);
3093 out << ')';
3094 }
3095 else
3096 convert_expr(src);
3097 }
3098 else
3099 UNEXPECTEDCASE("Unknown typecast "+src_type.id_string()+" -> float");
3100 }
3101 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_integer)
3102 {
3103 if(src_type.id()==ID_bool)
3104 {
3105 out << "(ite ";
3106 convert_expr(src);
3107 out <<" 1 0)";
3108 }
3109 else
3110 UNEXPECTEDCASE("Unknown typecast "+src_type.id_string()+" -> integer");
3111 }
3112 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_c_bit_field)
3113 {
3114 std::size_t from_width=boolbv_width(src_type);
3115 std::size_t to_width=boolbv_width(dest_type);
3116
3117 if(from_width==to_width)
3118 convert_expr(src); // ignore
3119 else
3120 {
3121 typet t=c_bit_field_replacement_type(to_c_bit_field_type(dest_type), ns);
3122 typecast_exprt tmp(typecast_exprt(src, t), dest_type);
3123 convert_typecast(tmp);
3124 }
3125 }
3126 else
3127 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
3128 "TODO typecast8 "+src_type.id_string()+" -> "+dest_type.id_string());
3129}
3130
3131void smt2_convt::convert_floatbv_typecast(const floatbv_typecast_exprt &expr)
3132{
3133 const exprt &src=expr.op();
3134 // const exprt &rounding_mode=expr.rounding_mode();
3135 const typet &src_type=src.type();
3136 const typet &dest_type=expr.type();
3137
3138 if(dest_type.id()==ID_floatbv)
3139 {
3140 if(src_type.id()==ID_floatbv)
3141 {
3142 // float to float
3143
3144 /* ISO 9899:1999
3145 * 6.3.1.5 Real floating types
3146 * 1 When a float is promoted to double or long double, or a
3147 * double is promoted to long double, its value is unchanged.
3148 *
3149 * 2 When a double is demoted to float, a long double is
3150 * demoted to double or float, or a value being represented in
3151 * greater precision and range than required by its semantic
3152 * type (see 6.3.1.8) is explicitly converted to its semantic
3153 * type, if the value being converted can be represented
3154 * exactly in the new type, it is unchanged. If the value
3155 * being converted is in the range of values that can be
3156 * represented but cannot be represented exactly, the result
3157 * is either the nearest higher or nearest lower representable
3158 * value, chosen in an implementation-defined manner. If the
3159 * value being converted is outside the range of values that
3160 * can be represented, the behavior is undefined.
3161 */
3162
3163 const floatbv_typet &dst=to_floatbv_type(dest_type);
3164
3165 if(use_FPA_theory)
3166 {
3167 out << "((_ to_fp " << dst.get_e() << " "
3168 << dst.get_f() + 1 << ") ";
3169 convert_rounding_mode_FPA(expr.op1());
3170 out << " ";
3171 convert_expr(src);
3172 out << ")";
3173 }
3174 else
3175 convert_floatbv(expr);
3176 }
3177 else if(src_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv)
3178 {
3179 // unsigned to float
3180
3181 /* ISO 9899:1999
3182 * 6.3.1.4 Real floating and integer
3183 * 2 When a value of integer type is converted to a real
3184 * floating type, if the value being converted can be
3185 * represented exactly in the new type, it is unchanged. If the
3186 * value being converted is in the range of values that can be
3187 * represented but cannot be represented exactly, the result is
3188 * either the nearest higher or nearest lower representable
3189 * value, chosen in an implementation-defined manner. If the
3190 * value being converted is outside the range of values that can
3191 * be represented, the behavior is undefined.
3192 */
3193
3194 const floatbv_typet &dst=to_floatbv_type(dest_type);
3195
3196 if(use_FPA_theory)
3197 {
3198 out << "((_ to_fp_unsigned " << dst.get_e() << " "
3199 << dst.get_f() + 1 << ") ";
3200 convert_rounding_mode_FPA(expr.op1());
3201 out << " ";
3202 convert_expr(src);
3203 out << ")";
3204 }
3205 else
3206 convert_floatbv(expr);
3207 }
3208 else if(src_type.id()==ID_signedbv)
3209 {
3210 // signed to float
3211
3212 const floatbv_typet &dst=to_floatbv_type(dest_type);
3213
3214 if(use_FPA_theory)
3215 {
3216 out << "((_ to_fp " << dst.get_e() << " "
3217 << dst.get_f() + 1 << ") ";
3218 convert_rounding_mode_FPA(expr.op1());
3219 out << " ";
3220 convert_expr(src);
3221 out << ")";
3222 }
3223 else
3224 convert_floatbv(expr);
3225 }
3226 else if(src_type.id()==ID_c_enum_tag)
3227 {
3228 // enum to float
3229
3230 // We first convert to 'underlying type'
3231 floatbv_typecast_exprt tmp=expr;
3232 tmp.op() = typecast_exprt(
3233 src, ns.follow_tag(to_c_enum_tag_type(src_type)).underlying_type());
3234 convert_floatbv_typecast(tmp);
3235 }
3236 else
3237 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
3238 "TODO typecast11 "+src_type.id_string()+" -> "+dest_type.id_string());
3239 }
3240 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_signedbv)
3241 {
3242 if(use_FPA_theory)
3243 {
3244 std::size_t dest_width=to_signedbv_type(dest_type).get_width();
3245 out << "((_ fp.to_sbv " << dest_width << ") ";
3246 convert_rounding_mode_FPA(expr.op1());
3247 out << " ";
3248 convert_expr(src);
3249 out << ")";
3250 }
3251 else
3252 convert_floatbv(expr);
3253 }
3254 else if(dest_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv)
3255 {
3256 if(use_FPA_theory)
3257 {
3258 std::size_t dest_width=to_unsignedbv_type(dest_type).get_width();
3259 out << "((_ fp.to_ubv " << dest_width << ") ";
3260 convert_rounding_mode_FPA(expr.op1());
3261 out << " ";
3262 convert_expr(src);
3263 out << ")";
3264 }
3265 else
3266 convert_floatbv(expr);
3267 }
3268 else
3269 {
3270 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
3271 "TODO typecast12 "+src_type.id_string()+" -> "+dest_type.id_string());
3272 }
3273}
3274
3275void smt2_convt::convert_struct(const struct_exprt &expr)
3276{
3277 const struct_typet &struct_type =
3278 expr.type().id() == ID_struct_tag
3279 ? ns.follow_tag(to_struct_tag_type(expr.type()))
3280 : to_struct_type(expr.type());
3281
3282 const struct_typet::componentst &components=
3283 struct_type.components();
3284
3285 DATA_INVARIANT(
3286 components.size() == expr.operands().size(),
3287 "number of struct components as indicated by the struct type shall be equal"
3288 "to the number of operands of the struct expression");
3289
3290 DATA_INVARIANT(!components.empty(), "struct shall have struct components");
3291
3292 if(use_datatypes)
3293 {
3294 const std::string &smt_typename = datatype_map.at(struct_type);
3295
3296 // use the constructor for the Z3 datatype
3297 out << "(mk-" << smt_typename;
3298
3299 std::size_t i=0;
3300 for(struct_typet::componentst::const_iterator
3301 it=components.begin();
3302 it!=components.end();
3303 it++, i++)
3304 {
3305 if(is_zero_width(it->type(), ns))
3306 continue;
3307 out << " ";
3308 convert_expr(expr.operands()[i]);
3309 }
3310
3311 out << ")";
3312 }
3313 else
3314 {
3315 auto convert_operand = [this](const exprt &op) {
3316 // may need to flatten array-theory arrays in there
3317 if(op.type().id() == ID_array && use_array_theory(op))
3318 flatten_array(op);
3319 else if(op.type().id() == ID_bool)
3320 flatten2bv(op);
3321 else
3322 convert_expr(op);
3323 };
3324
3325 // SMT-LIB 2 concat is binary only
3326 std::size_t n_concat = 0;
3327 for(std::size_t i = components.size(); i > 1; i--)
3328 {
3329 if(is_zero_width(components[i - 1].type(), ns))
3330 continue;
3331 else if(i > 2 || !is_zero_width(components[0].type(), ns))
3332 {
3333 ++n_concat;
3334 out << "(concat ";
3335 }
3336
3337 convert_operand(expr.operands()[i - 1]);
3338
3339 out << " ";
3340 }
3341
3342 if(!is_zero_width(components[0].type(), ns))
3343 convert_operand(expr.op0());
3344
3345 out << std::string(n_concat, ')');
3346 }
3347}
3348
3350void smt2_convt::flatten_array(const exprt &expr)
3351{
3352 const array_typet &array_type = to_array_type(expr.type());
3353 const auto &size_expr = array_type.size();
3354 PRECONDITION(size_expr.is_constant());
3355
3356 mp_integer size = numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(to_constant_expr(size_expr));
3357 CHECK_RETURN_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(size != 0, "can't convert zero-sized array");
3358
3359 out << "(let ((?far ";
3360 convert_expr(expr);
3361 out << ")) ";
3362
3363 for(mp_integer i=size; i!=0; --i)
3364 {
3365 if(i!=1)
3366 out << "(concat ";
3367 out << "(select ?far ";
3368 convert_expr(from_integer(i - 1, array_type.index_type()));
3369 out << ")";
3370 if(i!=1)
3371 out << " ";
3372 }
3373
3374 // close the many parentheses
3375 for(mp_integer i=size; i>1; --i)
3376 out << ")";
3377
3378 out << ")"; // let
3379}
3380
3381void smt2_convt::convert_union(const union_exprt &expr)
3382{
3383 const exprt &op=expr.op();
3384
3385 std::size_t total_width = boolbv_width(expr.type());
3386
3387 std::size_t member_width=boolbv_width(op.type());
3388
3389 if(total_width==member_width)
3390 {
3391 flatten2bv(op);
3392 }
3393 else
3394 {
3395 // we will pad with zeros, but non-det would be better
3396 INVARIANT(
3397 total_width > member_width,
3398 "total_width should be greater than member_width as member_width can be"
3399 "at most as large as total_width and the other case has been handled "
3400 "above");
3401 out << "(concat ";
3402 out << "(_ bv0 "
3403 << (total_width-member_width) << ") ";
3404 flatten2bv(op);
3405 out << ")";
3406 }
3407}
3408
3409void smt2_convt::convert_constant(const constant_exprt &expr)
3410{
3411 const typet &expr_type=expr.type();
3412
3413 if(expr_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv ||
3414 expr_type.id()==ID_signedbv ||
3415 expr_type.id()==ID_bv ||
3416 expr_type.id()==ID_c_enum ||
3417 expr_type.id()==ID_c_enum_tag ||
3418 expr_type.id()==ID_c_bool ||
3419 expr_type.id()==ID_c_bit_field)
3420 {
3421 const std::size_t width = boolbv_width(expr_type);
3422
3423 const mp_integer value = bvrep2integer(expr.get_value(), width, false);
3424
3425 out << "(_ bv" << value
3426 << " " << width << ")";
3427 }
3428 else if(expr_type.id()==ID_fixedbv)
3429 {
3430 const fixedbv_spect spec(to_fixedbv_type(expr_type));
3431
3432 const mp_integer v = bvrep2integer(expr.get_value(), spec.width, false);
3433
3434 out << "(_ bv" << v << " " << spec.width << ")";
3435 }
3436 else if(expr_type.id()==ID_floatbv)
3437 {
3438 const floatbv_typet &floatbv_type=
3439 to_floatbv_type(expr_type);
3440
3441 if(use_FPA_theory)
3442 {
3443 /* CBMC stores floating point literals in the most
3444 computationally useful form; biased exponents and
3445 significands including the hidden bit. Thus some encoding
3446 is needed to get to IEEE-754 style representations. */
3447
3448 ieee_floatt v=ieee_floatt(expr);
3449 size_t e=floatbv_type.get_e();
3450 size_t f=floatbv_type.get_f()+1;
3451
3452 /* Should be sufficient, but not currently supported by mathsat */
3453 #if 0
3454 mp_integer binary = v.pack();
3455
3456 out << "((_ to_fp " << e << " " << f << ")"
3457 << " #b" << integer2binary(v.pack(), v.spec.width()) << ")";
3458 #endif
3459
3460 if(v.is_NaN())
3461 {
3462 out << "(_ NaN " << e << " " << f << ")";
3463 }
3464 else if(v.is_infinity())
3465 {
3466 if(v.get_sign())
3467 out << "(_ -oo " << e << " " << f << ")";
3468 else
3469 out << "(_ +oo " << e << " " << f << ")";
3470 }
3471 else
3472 {
3473 // Zero, normal or subnormal
3474
3475 mp_integer binary = v.pack();
3476 std::string binaryString(integer2binary(v.pack(), v.spec.width()));
3477
3478 out << "(fp "
3479 << "#b" << binaryString.substr(0, 1) << " "
3480 << "#b" << binaryString.substr(1, e) << " "
3481 << "#b" << binaryString.substr(1+e, f-1) << ")";
3482 }
3483 }
3484 else
3485 {
3486 // produce corresponding bit-vector
3487 const ieee_float_spect spec(floatbv_type);
3488 const mp_integer v = bvrep2integer(expr.get_value(), spec.width(), false);
3489 out << "(_ bv" << v << " " << spec.width() << ")";
3490 }
3491 }
3492 else if(expr_type.id()==ID_pointer)
3493 {
3494 if(expr.is_null_pointer())
3495 {
3496 out << "(_ bv0 " << boolbv_width(expr_type)
3497 << ")";
3498 }
3499 else
3500 {
3501 // just treat the pointer as a bit vector
3502 const std::size_t width = boolbv_width(expr_type);
3503
3504 const mp_integer value = bvrep2integer(expr.get_value(), width, false);
3505
3506 out << "(_ bv" << value << " " << width << ")";
3507 }
3508 }
3509 else if(expr_type.id()==ID_bool)
3510 {
3511 if(expr.is_true())
3512 out << "true";
3513 else if(expr.is_false())
3514 out << "false";
3515 else
3516 UNEXPECTEDCASE("unknown Boolean constant");
3517 }
3518 else if(expr_type.id()==ID_array)
3519 {
3520 defined_expressionst::const_iterator it=defined_expressions.find(expr);
3521 CHECK_RETURN(it != defined_expressions.end());
3522 out << it->second;
3523 }
3524 else if(expr_type.id()==ID_rational)
3525 {
3526 std::string value=id2string(expr.get_value());
3527 const bool negative = has_prefix(value, "-");
3528
3529 if(negative)
3530 out << "(- ";
3531
3532 size_t pos=value.find("/");
3533
3534 if(pos==std::string::npos)
3535 out << value << ".0";
3536 else
3537 {
3538 out << "(/ " << value.substr(0, pos) << ".0 "
3539 << value.substr(pos+1) << ".0)";
3540 }
3541
3542 if(negative)
3543 out << ')';
3544 }
3545 else if(expr_type.id()==ID_integer)
3546 {
3547 const auto value = id2string(expr.get_value());
3548
3549 // SMT2 has no negative integer literals
3550 if(has_prefix(value, "-"))
3551 out << "(- " << value.substr(1, std::string::npos) << ')';
3552 else
3553 out << value;
3554 }
3555 else if(expr_type.id() == ID_range)
3556 {
3557 auto &range_type = to_range_type(expr_type);
3558 const auto size = range_type.get_to() - range_type.get_from() + 1;
3559 const auto width = address_bits(size);
3560 const auto value_int = numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(expr);
3561 out << "(_ bv" << (value_int - range_type.get_from()) << " " << width
3562 << ")";
3563 }
3564 else
3565 UNEXPECTEDCASE("unknown constant: "+expr_type.id_string());
3566}
