3602void smt2_convt::convert_is_dynamic_object(const unary_exprt &expr)
3603{
3604 std::vector<mp_integer> dynamic_objects;
3605 pointer_logic.get_dynamic_objects(dynamic_objects);
3606
3607 if(dynamic_objects.empty())
3608 out << "false";
3609 else
3610 {
3611 std::size_t pointer_width = boolbv_width(expr.op().type());
3612
3613 out << "(let ((?obj ((_ extract "
3614 << pointer_width-1 << " "
3615 << pointer_width-config.bv_encoding.object_bits << ") ";
3616 convert_expr(expr.op());
3617 out << "))) ";
3618
3619 if(dynamic_objects.size()==1)
3620 {
3621 out << "(= (_ bv" << dynamic_objects.front()
3622 << " " << config.bv_encoding.object_bits << ") ?obj)";
3623 }
3624 else
3625 {
3626 out << "(or";
3627
3628 for(const auto &object : dynamic_objects)
3629 out << " (= (_ bv" << object
3630 << " " << config.bv_encoding.object_bits << ") ?obj)";
3631
3632 out << ")"; // or
3633 }
3634
3635 out << ")"; // let
3636 }

3639void smt2_convt::convert_relation(const binary_relation_exprt &expr)
3640{
3641 const typet &op_type=expr.op0().type();
3642
3643 if(
3644 op_type.id() == ID_unsignedbv || op_type.id() == ID_bv ||
3645 op_type.id() == ID_range)
3646 {
3647 // The range type is encoded in binary
3648 out << "(";
3649 if(expr.id()==ID_le)
3650 out << "bvule";
3651 else if(expr.id()==ID_lt)
3652 out << "bvult";
3653 else if(expr.id()==ID_ge)
3654 out << "bvuge";
3655 else if(expr.id()==ID_gt)
3656 out << "bvugt";
3657
3658 out << " ";
3659 convert_expr(expr.op0());
3660 out << " ";
3661 convert_expr(expr.op1());
3662 out << ")";
3663 }
3664 else if(op_type.id()==ID_signedbv ||
3665 op_type.id()==ID_fixedbv)
3666 {
3667 out << "(";
3668 if(expr.id()==ID_le)
3669 out << "bvsle";
3670 else if(expr.id()==ID_lt)
3671 out << "bvslt";
3672 else if(expr.id()==ID_ge)
3673 out << "bvsge";
3674 else if(expr.id()==ID_gt)
3675 out << "bvsgt";
3676
3677 out << " ";
3678 convert_expr(expr.op0());
3679 out << " ";
3680 convert_expr(expr.op1());
3681 out << ")";
3682 }
3683 else if(op_type.id()==ID_floatbv)
3684 {
3685 if(use_FPA_theory)
3686 {
3687 out << "(";
3688 if(expr.id()==ID_le)
3689 out << "fp.leq";
3690 else if(expr.id()==ID_lt)
3691 out << "fp.lt";
3692 else if(expr.id()==ID_ge)
3693 out << "fp.geq";
3694 else if(expr.id()==ID_gt)
3695 out << "fp.gt";
3696
3697 out << " ";
3698 convert_expr(expr.op0());
3699 out << " ";
3700 convert_expr(expr.op1());
3701 out << ")";
3702 }
3703 else
3704 convert_floatbv(expr);
3705 }
3706 else if(op_type.id()==ID_rational ||
3707 op_type.id()==ID_integer)
3708 {
3709 out << "(";
3710 out << expr.id();
3711
3712 out << " ";
3713 convert_expr(expr.op0());
3714 out << " ";
3715 convert_expr(expr.op1());
3716 out << ")";
3717 }
3718 else if(op_type.id() == ID_pointer)
3719 {
3720 const exprt same_object = ::same_object(expr.op0(), expr.op1());
3721
3722 out << "(and ";
3723 convert_expr(same_object);
3724
3725 out << " (";
3726 if(expr.id() == ID_le)
3727 out << "bvsle";
3728 else if(expr.id() == ID_lt)
3729 out << "bvslt";
3730 else if(expr.id() == ID_ge)
3731 out << "bvsge";
3732 else if(expr.id() == ID_gt)
3733 out << "bvsgt";
3734
3735 out << ' ';
3736 convert_expr(pointer_offset(expr.op0()));
3737 out << ' ';
3738 convert_expr(pointer_offset(expr.op1()));
3739 out << ')';
3740
3741 out << ')';
3742 }
3743 else
3744 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
3745 "unsupported type for "+expr.id_string()+": "+op_type.id_string());
3746}
3747
3748void smt2_convt::convert_plus(const plus_exprt &expr)
3749{
3750 if(
3751 expr.type().id() == ID_rational || expr.type().id() == ID_integer ||
3752 expr.type().id() == ID_real)
3753 {
3754 // these are multi-ary in SMT-LIB2
3755 out << "(+";
3756
3757 for(const auto &op : expr.operands())
3758 {
3759 out << ' ';
3760 convert_expr(op);
3761 }
3762
3763 out << ')';
3764 }
3765 else if(
3766 expr.type().id() == ID_unsignedbv || expr.type().id() == ID_signedbv ||
3767 expr.type().id() == ID_fixedbv || expr.type().id() == ID_range)
3768 {
3769 // These could be chained, i.e., need not be binary,
3770 // but at least MathSat doesn't like that.
3771 if(expr.operands().size() == 2)
3772 {
3773 out << "(bvadd ";
3774 convert_expr(expr.op0());
3775 out << " ";
3776 convert_expr(expr.op1());
3777 out << ")";
3778 }
3779 else
3780 {
3781 convert_plus(to_plus_expr(make_binary(expr)));
3782 }
3783 }
3784 else if(expr.type().id() == ID_floatbv)
3785 {
3786 // Floating-point additions should have be been converted
3787 // to ID_floatbv_plus during symbolic execution, adding
3788 // the rounding mode. See smt2_convt::convert_floatbv_plus.
3789 UNREACHABLE;
3790 }
3791 else if(expr.type().id() == ID_pointer)
3792 {
3793 if(expr.operands().size() == 2)
3794 {
3795 exprt p = expr.op0(), i = expr.op1();
3796
3797 if(p.type().id() != ID_pointer)
3798 p.swap(i);
3799
3800 DATA_INVARIANT(
3801 p.type().id() == ID_pointer,
3802 "one of the operands should have pointer type");
3803
3804 const auto &base_type = to_pointer_type(expr.type()).base_type();
3805 DATA_INVARIANT(
3806 base_type.id() != ID_empty, "no pointer arithmetic over void pointers");
3807
3808 auto element_size_opt = pointer_offset_size(base_type, ns);
3809 CHECK_RETURN(element_size_opt.has_value() && *element_size_opt >= 0);
3810 mp_integer element_size = *element_size_opt;
3811
3812 // First convert the pointer operand
3813 out << "(let ((?pointerop ";
3814 convert_expr(p);
3815 out << ")) ";
3816
3817 // The addition is done on the offset part only.
3818 const std::size_t pointer_width = boolbv_width(p.type());
3819 const std::size_t offset_bits =
3820 pointer_width - config.bv_encoding.object_bits;
3821
3822 out << "(concat ";
3823 out << "((_ extract " << pointer_width - 1 << ' ' << offset_bits
3824 << ") ?pointerop) ";
3825 out << "(bvadd ((_ extract " << offset_bits - 1 << " 0) ?pointerop) ";
3826
3827 if(element_size >= 2)
3828 {
3829 out << "(bvmul ((_ extract " << offset_bits - 1 << " 0) ";
3830 convert_expr(i);
3831 out << ") (_ bv" << element_size << " " << offset_bits << "))";
3832 }
3833 else
3834 {
3835 out << "((_ extract " << offset_bits - 1 << " 0) ";
3836 convert_expr(i);
3837 out << ')'; // extract
3838 }
3839
3840 out << ")))"; // bvadd, concat, let
3841 }
3842 else
3843 {
3844 convert_plus(to_plus_expr(make_binary(expr)));
3845 }
3846 }
3847 else
3848 UNEXPECTEDCASE("unsupported type for +: " + expr.type().id_string());
3849}
3850
3854void smt2_convt::convert_rounding_mode_FPA(const exprt &expr)
3855{
3856 PRECONDITION(use_FPA_theory);
3857
3858 /* CProver uses the x86 numbering of the rounding-mode
3859 * 0 == FE_TONEAREST
3860 * 1 == FE_DOWNWARD
3861 * 2 == FE_UPWARD
3862 * 3 == FE_TOWARDZERO
3863 * These literal values must be used rather than the macros
3864 * the macros from fenv.h to avoid portability problems.
3865 */
3866
3867 if(expr.is_constant())
3868 {
3869 const constant_exprt &cexpr=to_constant_expr(expr);
3870
3871 mp_integer value = numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(cexpr);
3872
3873 if(value==0)
3874 out << "roundNearestTiesToEven";
3875 else if(value==1)
3876 out << "roundTowardNegative";
3877 else if(value==2)
3878 out << "roundTowardPositive";
3879 else if(value==3)
3880 out << "roundTowardZero";
3881 else
3882 INVARIANT_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(
3883 false,
3884 "Rounding mode should have value 0, 1, 2, or 3",
3885 id2string(cexpr.get_value()));
3886 }
3887 else
3888 {
3889 std::size_t width=to_bitvector_type(expr.type()).get_width();
3890
3891 // Need to make the choice above part of the model
3892 out << "(ite (= (_ bv0 " << width << ") ";
3893 convert_expr(expr);
3894 out << ") roundNearestTiesToEven ";
3895
3896 out << "(ite (= (_ bv1 " << width << ") ";
3897 convert_expr(expr);
3898 out << ") roundTowardNegative ";
3899
3900 out << "(ite (= (_ bv2 " << width << ") ";
3901 convert_expr(expr);
3902 out << ") roundTowardPositive ";
3903
3904 // TODO: add some kind of error checking here
3905 out << "roundTowardZero";
3906
3907 out << ")))";
3908 }
3909}

3946void smt2_convt::convert_minus(const minus_exprt &expr)
3947{
3948 if(expr.type().id()==ID_integer)
3949 {
3950 out << "(- ";
3951 convert_expr(expr.op0());
3952 out << " ";
3953 convert_expr(expr.op1());
3954 out << ")";
3955 }
3956 else if(expr.type().id()==ID_unsignedbv ||
3957 expr.type().id()==ID_signedbv ||
3958 expr.type().id()==ID_fixedbv)
3959 {
3960 if(expr.op0().type().id()==ID_pointer &&
3961 expr.op1().type().id()==ID_pointer)
3962 {
3963 // Pointer difference
3964 const auto &base_type = to_pointer_type(expr.op0().type()).base_type();
3965 DATA_INVARIANT(
3966 base_type.id() != ID_empty, "no pointer arithmetic over void pointers");
3967 auto element_size_opt = pointer_offset_size(base_type, ns);
3968 CHECK_RETURN(element_size_opt.has_value() && *element_size_opt >= 1);
3969 mp_integer element_size = *element_size_opt;
3970
3971 if(element_size >= 2)
3972 out << "(bvsdiv ";
3973
3974 INVARIANT(
3975 boolbv_width(expr.op0().type()) == boolbv_width(expr.type()),
3976 "bitvector width of operand shall be equal to the bitvector width of "
3977 "the expression");
3978
3979 out << "(bvsub ";
3980 convert_expr(expr.op0());
3981 out << " ";
3982 convert_expr(expr.op1());
3983 out << ")";
3984
3985 if(element_size >= 2)
3986 out << " (_ bv" << element_size << " " << boolbv_width(expr.type())
3987 << "))";
3988 }
3989 else
3990 {
3991 out << "(bvsub ";
3992 convert_expr(expr.op0());
3993 out << " ";
3994 convert_expr(expr.op1());
3995 out << ")";
3996 }
3997 }
3998 else if(expr.type().id()==ID_floatbv)
3999 {
4000 // Floating-point subtraction should have be been converted
4001 // to ID_floatbv_minus during symbolic execution, adding
4002 // the rounding mode. See smt2_convt::convert_floatbv_minus.
4003 UNREACHABLE;
4004 }
4005 else if(expr.type().id()==ID_pointer)
4006 {
4007 if(
4008 expr.op0().type().id() == ID_pointer &&
4009 (expr.op1().type().id() == ID_unsignedbv ||
4010 expr.op1().type().id() == ID_signedbv))
4011 {
4012 // rewrite p-o to p+(-o)
4013 return convert_plus(
4014 plus_exprt(expr.op0(), unary_minus_exprt(expr.op1())));
4015 }
4016 else
4017 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
4018 "unsupported operand types for -: " + expr.op0().type().id_string() +
4019 " and " + expr.op1().type().id_string());
4020 }
4021 else
4022 UNEXPECTEDCASE("unsupported type for -: "+expr.type().id_string());
4023}

4109void smt2_convt::convert_mult(const mult_exprt &expr)
4110{
4111 // re-write to binary if needed
4112 if(expr.operands().size()>2)
4113 {
4114 // strip last operand
4115 exprt tmp=expr;
4116 tmp.operands().pop_back();
4117
4118 // recursive call
4119 return convert_mult(mult_exprt(tmp, expr.operands().back()));
4120 }
4121
4122 INVARIANT(
4123 expr.operands().size() == 2,
4124 "expression should have been converted to a variant with two operands");
4125
4126 if(expr.type().id()==ID_unsignedbv ||
4127 expr.type().id()==ID_signedbv)
4128 {
4129 // Note that bvmul is really unsigned,
4130 // but this is irrelevant as we chop-off any extra result
4131 // bits.
4132 out << "(bvmul ";
4133 convert_expr(expr.op0());
4134 out << " ";
4135 convert_expr(expr.op1());
4136 out << ")";
4137 }
4138 else if(expr.type().id()==ID_floatbv)
4139 {
4140 // Floating-point multiplication should have be been converted
4141 // to ID_floatbv_mult during symbolic execution, adding
4142 // the rounding mode. See smt2_convt::convert_floatbv_mult.
4143 UNREACHABLE;
4144 }
4145 else if(expr.type().id()==ID_fixedbv)
4146 {
4147 fixedbv_spect spec(to_fixedbv_type(expr.type()));
4148 std::size_t fraction_bits=spec.get_fraction_bits();
4149
4150 out << "((_ extract "
4151 << spec.width+fraction_bits-1 << " "
4152 << fraction_bits << ") ";
4153
4154 out << "(bvmul ";
4155
4156 out << "((_ sign_extend " << fraction_bits << ") ";
4157 convert_expr(expr.op0());
4158 out << ") ";
4159
4160 out << "((_ sign_extend " << fraction_bits << ") ";
4161 convert_expr(expr.op1());
4162 out << ")";
4163
4164 out << "))"; // bvmul, extract
4165 }
4166 else if(expr.type().id()==ID_rational ||
4167 expr.type().id()==ID_integer ||
4168 expr.type().id()==ID_real)
4169 {
4170 out << "(*";
4171
4172 for(const auto &op : expr.operands())
4173 {
4174 out << " ";
4175 convert_expr(op);
4176 }
4177
4178 out << ")";
4179 }
4180 else
4181 UNEXPECTEDCASE("unsupported type for *: "+expr.type().id_string());
4182}

4226
4227void smt2_convt::convert_with(const with_exprt &expr)
4228{
4229 // get rid of "with" that has more than three operands
4230
4231 if(expr.operands().size()>3)
4232 {
4233 std::size_t s=expr.operands().size();
4234
4235 // strip off the trailing two operands
4236 with_exprt tmp = expr;
4237 tmp.operands().resize(s-2);
4238
4239 with_exprt new_with_expr(
4240 tmp, expr.operands()[s - 2], expr.operands().back());
4241
4242 // recursive call
4243 return convert_with(new_with_expr);
4244 }
4245
4246 INVARIANT(
4247 expr.operands().size() == 3,
4248 "with expression should have been converted to a version with three "
4249 "operands above");
4250
4251 const typet &expr_type = expr.type();
4252
4253 if(expr_type.id()==ID_array)
4254 {
4255 const array_typet &array_type=to_array_type(expr_type);
4256
4257 if(use_array_theory(expr))
4258 {
4259 out << "(store ";
4260 convert_expr(expr.old());
4261 out << " ";
4262 convert_expr(typecast_exprt(expr.where(), array_type.index_type()));
4263 out << " ";
4264 convert_expr(expr.new_value());
4265 out << ")";
4266 }
4267 else
4268 {
4269 // fixed-width
4270 std::size_t array_width=boolbv_width(array_type);
4271 std::size_t sub_width = boolbv_width(array_type.element_type());
4272 std::size_t index_width=boolbv_width(expr.where().type());
4273
4274 // We mask out the updated bits with AND,
4275 // and then OR-in the shifted new value.
4276
4277 out << "(let ((distance? ";
4278 out << "(bvmul (_ bv" << sub_width << " " << array_width << ") ";
4279
4280 // SMT2 says that the shift distance needs to be as wide
4281 // as the stuff we are shifting.
4282 if(array_width>index_width)
4283 {
4284 out << "((_ zero_extend " << array_width-index_width << ") ";
4285 convert_expr(expr.where());
4286 out << ")";
4287 }
4288 else
4289 {
4290 out << "((_ extract " << array_width-1 << " 0) ";
4291 convert_expr(expr.where());
4292 out << ")";
4293 }
4294
4295 out << "))) "; // bvmul, distance?
4296
4297 out << "(bvor ";
4298 out << "(bvand ";
4299 out << "(bvnot ";
4300 out << "(bvshl (_ bv" << power(2, sub_width) - 1 << " " << array_width
4301 << ") ";
4302 out << "distance?)) "; // bvnot, bvlshl
4303 convert_expr(expr.old());
4304 out << ") "; // bvand
4305 out << "(bvshl ";
4306 out << "((_ zero_extend " << array_width-sub_width << ") ";
4307 convert_expr(expr.new_value());
4308 out << ") distance?)))"; // zero_extend, bvshl, bvor, let
4309 }
4310 }
4311 else if(expr_type.id() == ID_struct || expr_type.id() == ID_struct_tag)
4312 {
4313 const struct_typet &struct_type =
4314 expr_type.id() == ID_struct_tag
4315 ? ns.follow_tag(to_struct_tag_type(expr_type))
4316 : to_struct_type(expr_type);
4317
4318 const exprt &index = expr.where();
4319 const exprt &value = expr.new_value();
4320
4321 const irep_idt &component_name=index.get(ID_component_name);
4322
4323 INVARIANT(
4324 struct_type.has_component(component_name),
4325 "struct should have accessed component");
4326
4327 if(use_datatypes)
4328 {
4329 const std::string &smt_typename = datatype_map.at(expr_type);
4330
4331 out << "(update-" << smt_typename << "." << component_name << " ";
4332 convert_expr(expr.old());
4333 out << " ";
4334 convert_expr(value);
4335 out << ")";
4336 }
4337 else
4338 {
4339 std::size_t struct_width=boolbv_width(struct_type);
4340
4341 // figure out the offset and width of the member
4342 const boolbv_widtht::membert &m =
4343 boolbv_width.get_member(struct_type, component_name);
4344
4345 out << "(let ((?withop ";
4346 convert_expr(expr.old());
4347 out << ")) ";
4348
4349 if(m.width==struct_width)
4350 {
4351 // the struct is the same as the member, no concat needed,
4352 // ?withop won't be used
4353 convert_expr(value);
4354 }
4355 else if(m.offset==0)
4356 {
4357 // the member is at the beginning
4358 out << "(concat "
4359 << "((_ extract " << (struct_width-1) << " "
4360 << m.width << ") ?withop) ";
4361 convert_expr(value);
4362 out << ")"; // concat
4363 }
4364 else if(m.offset+m.width==struct_width)
4365 {
4366 // the member is at the end
4367 out << "(concat ";
4368 convert_expr(value);
4369 out << " ((_ extract " << (m.offset - 1) << " 0) ?withop))";
4370 }
4371 else
4372 {
4373 // most general case, need two concat-s
4374 out << "(concat (concat "
4375 << "((_ extract " << (struct_width-1) << " "
4376 << (m.offset+m.width) << ") ?withop) ";
4377 convert_expr(value);
4378 out << ") ((_ extract " << (m.offset-1) << " 0) ?withop)";
4379 out << ")"; // concat
4380 }
4381
4382 out << ")"; // let ?withop
4383 }
4384 }
4385 else if(expr_type.id() == ID_union || expr_type.id() == ID_union_tag)
4386 {
4387 const exprt &value = expr.new_value();
4388
4389 std::size_t total_width = boolbv_width(expr_type);
4390
4391 std::size_t member_width=boolbv_width(value.type());
4392
4393 if(total_width==member_width)
4394 {
4395 flatten2bv(value);
4396 }
4397 else
4398 {
4399 INVARIANT(
4400 total_width > member_width,
4401 "total width should be greater than member_width as member_width is at "
4402 "most as large as total_width and the other case has been handled "
4403 "above");
4404 out << "(concat ";
4405 out << "((_ extract "
4406 << (total_width-1)
4407 << " " << member_width << ") ";
4408 convert_expr(expr.old());
4409 out << ") ";
4410 flatten2bv(value);
4411 out << ")";
4412 }
4413 }
4414 else if(expr_type.id()==ID_bv ||
4415 expr_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv ||
4416 expr_type.id()==ID_signedbv)
4417 {
4418 if(expr.new_value().type().id() == ID_bool)
4419 {
4420 convert_update_bit(
4421 update_bit_exprt(expr.old(), expr.where(), expr.new_value()));
4422 }
4423 else
4424 {
4425 convert_update_bits(
4426 update_bits_exprt(expr.old(), expr.where(), expr.new_value()));
4427 }
4428 }
4429 else
4430 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
4431 "with expects struct, union, or array type, but got "+
4432 expr.type().id_string());
4433}

4451
4452void smt2_convt::convert_index(const index_exprt &expr)
4453{
4454 const typet &array_op_type = expr.array().type();
4455
4456 if(array_op_type.id()==ID_array)
4457 {
4458 const array_typet &array_type=to_array_type(array_op_type);
4459
4460 if(use_array_theory(expr.array()))
4461 {
4462 if(expr.is_boolean() && !use_array_of_bool)
4463 {
4464 out << "(= ";
4465 out << "(select ";
4466 convert_expr(expr.array());
4467 out << " ";
4468 convert_expr(typecast_exprt(expr.index(), array_type.index_type()));
4469 out << ")";
4470 out << " #b1)";
4471 }
4472 else
4473 {
4474 out << "(select ";
4475 convert_expr(expr.array());
4476 out << " ";
4477 convert_expr(typecast_exprt(expr.index(), array_type.index_type()));
4478 out << ")";
4479 }
4480 }
4481 else
4482 {
4483 // fixed size
4484 std::size_t array_width=boolbv_width(array_type);
4485
4486 unflatten(wheret::BEGIN, array_type.element_type());
4487
4488 std::size_t sub_width = boolbv_width(array_type.element_type());
4489 std::size_t index_width=boolbv_width(expr.index().type());
4490
4491 out << "((_ extract " << sub_width-1 << " 0) ";
4492 out << "(bvlshr ";
4493 convert_expr(expr.array());
4494 out << " ";
4495 out << "(bvmul (_ bv" << sub_width << " " << array_width << ") ";
4496
4497 // SMT2 says that the shift distance must be the same as
4498 // the width of what we shift.
4499 if(array_width>index_width)
4500 {
4501 out << "((_ zero_extend " << array_width-index_width << ") ";
4502 convert_expr(expr.index());
4503 out << ")"; // zero_extend
4504 }
4505 else
4506 {
4507 out << "((_ extract " << array_width-1 << " 0) ";
4508 convert_expr(expr.index());
4509 out << ")"; // extract
4510 }
4511
4512 out << ")))"; // mult, bvlshr, extract
4513
4514 unflatten(wheret::END, array_type.element_type());
4515 }
4516 }
4517 else
4518 INVARIANT(
4519 false, "index with unsupported array type: " + array_op_type.id_string());
4520}
4521
4522void smt2_convt::convert_member(const member_exprt &expr)
4523{
4524 const member_exprt &member_expr=to_member_expr(expr);
4525 const exprt &struct_op=member_expr.struct_op();
4526 const typet &struct_op_type = struct_op.type();
4527 const irep_idt &name=member_expr.get_component_name();
4528
4529 if(struct_op_type.id() == ID_struct || struct_op_type.id() == ID_struct_tag)
4530 {
4531 const struct_typet &struct_type =
4532 struct_op_type.id() == ID_struct_tag
4533 ? ns.follow_tag(to_struct_tag_type(struct_op_type))
4534 : to_struct_type(struct_op_type);
4535
4536 INVARIANT(
4537 struct_type.has_component(name), "struct should have accessed component");
4538
4539 if(use_datatypes)
4540 {
4541 const std::string &smt_typename = datatype_map.at(struct_type);
4542
4543 out << "(" << smt_typename << "."
4544 << struct_type.get_component(name).get_name()
4545 << " ";
4546 convert_expr(struct_op);
4547 out << ")";
4548 }
4549 else
4550 {
4551 // we extract
4552 const auto &member_offset = boolbv_width.get_member(struct_type, name);
4553
4554 if(expr.type().id() == ID_bool)
4555 out << "(= ";
4556 out << "((_ extract " << (member_offset.offset + member_offset.width - 1)
4557 << " " << member_offset.offset << ") ";
4558 convert_expr(struct_op);
4559 out << ")";
4560 if(expr.type().id() == ID_bool)
4561 out << " #b1)";
4562 }
4563 }
4564 else if(
4565 struct_op_type.id() == ID_union || struct_op_type.id() == ID_union_tag)
4566 {
4567 std::size_t width=boolbv_width(expr.type());
4568 CHECK_RETURN_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(
4569 width != 0, "failed to get union member width");
4570
4571 if(use_datatypes)
4572 {
4573 unflatten(wheret::BEGIN, expr.type());
4574
4575 out << "((_ extract " << (width - 1) << " 0) ";
4576 convert_expr(struct_op);
4577 out << ")";
4578
4579 unflatten(wheret::END, expr.type());
4580 }
4581 else
4582 {
4583 out << "((_ extract " << (width - 1) << " 0) ";
4584 convert_expr(struct_op);
4585 out << ")";
4586 }
4587 }
4588 else
4589 UNEXPECTEDCASE(
4590 "convert_member on an unexpected type "+struct_op_type.id_string());
4591}
4592
4593void smt2_convt::flatten2bv(const exprt &expr)
4594{
4595 const typet &type = expr.type();
4596
4597 if(type.id()==ID_bool)
4598 {
4599 out << "(ite ";
4600 convert_expr(expr); // this returns a Bool
4601 out << " #b1 #b0)"; // this is a one-bit bit-vector
4602 }
4603 else if(type.id()==ID_array)
4604 {
4605 if(use_array_theory(expr))
4606 {
4607 // concatenate elements
4608 const array_typet &array_type = to_array_type(type);
4609
4610 mp_integer size =
4611 numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(to_constant_expr(array_type.size()));
4612
4613 // SMT-LIB 2 concat is binary only
4614 std::size_t n_concat = 0;
4615 for(mp_integer i = size; i > 1; --i)
4616 {
4617 ++n_concat;
4618 out << "(concat ";
4619
4620 flatten2bv(
4621 index_exprt{expr, from_integer(i - 1, array_type.index_type())});
4622
4623 out << " ";
4624 }
4625
4626 flatten2bv(index_exprt{expr, from_integer(0, array_type.index_type())});
4627
4628 out << std::string(n_concat, ')'); // concat
4629 }
4630 else
4631 convert_expr(expr);
4632 }
4633 else if(type.id() == ID_struct || type.id() == ID_struct_tag)
4634 {
4635 if(use_datatypes)
4636 {
4637 // concatenate elements
4638 const struct_typet &struct_type =
4639 type.id() == ID_struct_tag ? ns.follow_tag(to_struct_tag_type(type))
4640 : to_struct_type(type);
4641
4642 const struct_typet::componentst &components=
4643 struct_type.components();
4644
4645 // SMT-LIB 2 concat is binary only
4646 std::size_t n_concat = 0;
4647 for(std::size_t i=components.size(); i>1; i--)
4648 {
4649 if(is_zero_width(components[i - 1].type(), ns))
4650 continue;
4651 else if(i > 2 || !is_zero_width(components[0].type(), ns))
4652 {
4653 ++n_concat;
4654 out << "(concat ";
4655 }
4656
4657 flatten2bv(member_exprt{expr, components[i - 1]});
4658
4659 out << " ";
4660 }
4661
4662 if(!is_zero_width(components[0].type(), ns))
4663 {
4664 flatten2bv(member_exprt{expr, components[0]});
4665 }
4666
4667 out << std::string(n_concat, ')'); // concat
4668 }
4669 else
4670 convert_expr(expr);
4671 }
4672 else if(type.id()==ID_floatbv)
4673 {
4674 INVARIANT(
4675 !use_FPA_theory,
4676 "floatbv expressions should be flattened when using FPA theory");
4677
4678 convert_expr(expr);
4679 }
4680 else
4681 convert_expr(expr);
4682}
4683
4684void smt2_convt::unflatten(
4685 wheret where,
4686 const typet &type,
4687 unsigned nesting)
4688{
4689 if(type.id()==ID_bool)
4690 {
4691 if(where==wheret::BEGIN)
4692 out << "(= "; // produces a bool
4693 else
4694 out << " #b1)";
4695 }
4696 else if(type.id() == ID_array)
4697 {
4698 PRECONDITION(use_as_const);
4699
4700 if(where == wheret::BEGIN)
4701 out << "(let ((?ufop" << nesting << " ";
4702 else
4703 {
4704 out << ")) ";
4705
4706 const array_typet &array_type = to_array_type(type);
4707
4708 std::size_t subtype_width = boolbv_width(array_type.element_type());
4709
4710 DATA_INVARIANT(
4711 array_type.size().is_constant(),
4712 "cannot unflatten arrays of non-constant size");
4713 mp_integer size =
4714 numeric_cast_v<mp_integer>(to_constant_expr(array_type.size()));
4715
4716 for(mp_integer i = 1; i < size; ++i)
4717 out << "(store ";
4718
4719 out << "((as const ";
4720 convert_type(array_type);
4721 out << ") ";
4722 // use element at index 0 as default value
4723 unflatten(wheret::BEGIN, array_type.element_type(), nesting + 1);
4724 out << "((_ extract " << subtype_width - 1 << " "
4725 << "0) ?ufop" << nesting << ")";
4726 unflatten(wheret::END, array_type.element_type(), nesting + 1);
4727 out << ") ";
4728
4729 std::size_t offset = subtype_width;
4730 for(mp_integer i = 1; i < size; ++i, offset += subtype_width)
4731 {
4732 convert_expr(from_integer(i, array_type.index_type()));
4733 out << ' ';
4734 unflatten(wheret::BEGIN, array_type.element_type(), nesting + 1);
4735 out << "((_ extract " << offset + subtype_width - 1 << " " << offset
4736 << ") ?ufop" << nesting << ")";
4737 unflatten(wheret::END, array_type.element_type(), nesting + 1);
4738 out << ")"; // store
4739 }
4740
4741 out << ")"; // let
4742 }
4743 }
4744 else if(type.id() == ID_struct || type.id() == ID_struct_tag)
4745 {
4746 if(use_datatypes)
4747 {
4748 // extract members
4749 if(where==wheret::BEGIN)
4750 out << "(let ((?ufop" << nesting << " ";
4751 else
4752 {
4753 out << ")) ";
4754
4755 const std::string &smt_typename = datatype_map.at(type);
4756
4757 out << "(mk-" << smt_typename;
4758
4759 const struct_typet &struct_type =
4760 type.id() == ID_struct_tag ? ns.follow_tag(to_struct_tag_type(type))
4761 : to_struct_type(type);
4762
4763 const struct_typet::componentst &components=
4764 struct_type.components();
4765
4766 std::size_t offset=0;
4767
4768 std::size_t i=0;
4769 for(struct_typet::componentst::const_iterator
4770 it=components.begin();
4771 it!=components.end();
4772 it++, i++)
4773 {
4774 if(is_zero_width(it->type(), ns))
4775 continue;
4776
4777 std::size_t member_width=boolbv_width(it->type());
4778
4779 out << " ";
4780 unflatten(wheret::BEGIN, it->type(), nesting+1);
4781 out << "((_ extract " << offset+member_width-1 << " "
4782 << offset << ") ?ufop" << nesting << ")";
4783 unflatten(wheret::END, it->type(), nesting+1);
4784 offset+=member_width;
4785 }
4786
4787 out << "))"; // mk-, let
4788 }
4789 }
4790 else
4791 {
4792 // nop, already a bv
4793 }
4794 }
4795 else
4796 {
4797 // nop
4798 }
4799}
4800
4801void smt2_convt::set_to(const exprt &expr, bool value)
4802{
4803 PRECONDITION(expr.is_boolean());
4804
4805 if(expr.id()==ID_and && value)
4806 {
4807 for(const auto &op : expr.operands())
4808 set_to(op, true);
4809 return;
4810 }
4811
4812 if(expr.id()==ID_or && !value)
4813 {
4814 for(const auto &op : expr.operands())
4815 set_to(op, false);
4816 return;
4817 }
4818
4819 if(expr.id()==ID_not)
4820 {
4821 return set_to(to_not_expr(expr).op(), !value);
4822 }
4823
4824 out << "\n";
4825
4826 // special treatment for "set_to(a=b, true)" where
4827 // a is a new symbol
4828
4829 if(expr.id() == ID_equal && value)
4830 {
4831 const equal_exprt &equal_expr=to_equal_expr(expr);
4832 if(is_zero_width(equal_expr.lhs().type(), ns))
4833 {
4834 // ignore equality checking over expressions with empty (void) type
4835 return;
4836 }
4837
4838 if(equal_expr.lhs().id()==ID_symbol)
4839 {
4840 const irep_idt &identifier=
4841 to_symbol_expr(equal_expr.lhs()).get_identifier();
4842
4843 if(
4844 identifier_map.find(identifier) == identifier_map.end() &&
4845 equal_expr.lhs() != equal_expr.rhs())
4846 {
4847 auto id_entry = identifier_map.insert(
4848 {identifier, identifiert{equal_expr.lhs().type(), false}});
4849 CHECK_RETURN(id_entry.second);
4850
4851 find_symbols(id_entry.first->second.type);
4852 exprt prepared_rhs = prepare_for_convert_expr(equal_expr.rhs());
4853
4854 std::string smt2_identifier=convert_identifier(identifier);
4855 smt2_identifiers.insert(smt2_identifier);
4856
4857 out << "; set_to true (equal)\n";
4858
4859 if(equal_expr.lhs().type().id() == ID_mathematical_function)
4860 {
4861 // We avoid define-fun, since it has been reported to cause
4862 // trouble with Z3's parser.
4863 out << "(declare-fun " << smt2_identifier;
4864
4865 auto &mathematical_function_type =
4866 to_mathematical_function_type(equal_expr.lhs().type());
4867
4868 out << " (";
4869 bool first = true;
4870
4871 for(auto &t : mathematical_function_type.domain())
4872 {
4873 if(first)
4874 first = false;
4875 else
4876 out << ' ';
4877
4878 convert_type(t);
4879 }
4880
4881 out << ") ";
4882 convert_type(mathematical_function_type.codomain());
4883 out << ")\n";
4884
4885 out << "(assert (= " << smt2_identifier << ' ';
4886 convert_expr(prepared_rhs);
4887 out << ')' << ')' << '\n';
4888 }
4889 else
4890 {
4891 out << "(define-fun " << smt2_identifier;
4892 out << " () ";
4893 convert_type(equal_expr.lhs().type());
4894 out << ' ';
4895 if(
4896 equal_expr.lhs().type().id() != ID_array ||
4897 use_array_theory(prepared_rhs))
4898 {
4899 convert_expr(prepared_rhs);
4900 }
4901 else
4902 {
4903 unflatten(wheret::BEGIN, equal_expr.lhs().type());
4904
4905 convert_expr(prepared_rhs);
4906
4907 unflatten(wheret::END, equal_expr.lhs().type());
4908 }
4909 out << ')' << '\n';
4910 }
4911
4912 return; // done
4913 }
4914 }
4915 }
4916
4917 exprt prepared_expr = prepare_for_convert_expr(expr);
4918
4919#if 0
4920 out << "; CONV: "
4921 << format(expr) << "\n";
4922#endif
4923
4924 out << "; set_to " << (value?"true":"false") << "\n"
4925 << "(assert ";
4926 if(!value)
4927 {
4928 out << "(not ";
4929 }
4930 const auto found_literal = defined_expressions.find(expr);
4931 if(!(found_literal == defined_expressions.end()))
4932 {
4933 // This is a converted expression, we can just assert the literal name
4934 // since the expression is already defined
4935 out << found_literal->second;
4936 set_values[found_literal->second] = value;
4937 }
4938 else
4939 {
4940 convert_expr(prepared_expr);
4941 }
4942 if(!value)
4943 {
4944 out << ")";
4945 }
4946 out << ")\n";
4947 return;
4948}
4949
4956exprt smt2_convt::lower_byte_operators(const exprt &expr)
4957{
4958 exprt lowered_expr = expr;
4959
4960 for(auto it = lowered_expr.depth_begin(), itend = lowered_expr.depth_end();
4961 it != itend;
4962 ++it)
4963 {
4964 if(
4965 it->id() == ID_byte_extract_little_endian ||
4966 it->id() == ID_byte_extract_big_endian)
4967 {
4968 it.mutate() = lower_byte_extract(to_byte_extract_expr(*it), ns);
4969 }
4970 else if(
4971 it->id() == ID_byte_update_little_endian ||
4972 it->id() == ID_byte_update_big_endian)
4973 {
4974 it.mutate() = lower_byte_update(to_byte_update_expr(*it), ns);
4975 }
4976 }
4977
4978 return lowered_expr;
4979}
4980
4988exprt smt2_convt::prepare_for_convert_expr(const exprt &expr)
4989{
4990 // First, replace byte operators, because they may introduce new array
4991 // expressions that must be seen by find_symbols:
4992 exprt lowered_expr = lower_byte_operators(expr);
4993 INVARIANT(
4994 !has_byte_operator(lowered_expr),
4995 "lower_byte_operators should remove all byte operators");
4996
4997 // Perform rewrites that may introduce new symbols
4998 for(auto it = lowered_expr.depth_begin(), itend = lowered_expr.depth_end();
4999 it != itend;) // no ++it
5000 {
5001 if(
5002 auto prophecy_r_or_w_ok =
5003 expr_try_dynamic_cast<prophecy_r_or_w_ok_exprt>(*it))
5004 {
5005 exprt lowered = simplify_expr(prophecy_r_or_w_ok->lower(ns), ns);
5006 it.mutate() = lowered;
5007 it.next_sibling_or_parent();
5008 }
5009 else if(
5010 auto prophecy_pointer_in_range =
5011 expr_try_dynamic_cast<prophecy_pointer_in_range_exprt>(*it))
5012 {
5013 exprt lowered = simplify_expr(prophecy_pointer_in_range->lower(ns), ns);
5014 it.mutate() = lowered;
5015 it.next_sibling_or_parent();
5016 }
5017 else
5018 ++it;
5019 }
5020
5021 // Now create symbols for all composite expressions present in lowered_expr:
5022 find_symbols(lowered_expr);
5023
5024 return lowered_expr;
5025}
5026
5027void smt2_convt::find_symbols(const exprt &expr)
5028{
5029 if(is_zero_width(expr.type(), ns))
5030 return;
5031
5032 // recursive call on type
5033 find_symbols(expr.type());
5034
5035 if(expr.id() == ID_exists || expr.id() == ID_forall)
5036 {
5037 std::unordered_map<irep_idt, std::optional<identifiert>> shadowed_syms;
5038
5039 // do not declare the quantified symbol, but record
5040 // as 'bound symbol'
5041 const auto &q_expr = to_quantifier_expr(expr);
5042 for(const auto &symbol : q_expr.variables())
5043 {
5044 const auto identifier = symbol.get_identifier();
5045 auto id_entry =
5046 identifier_map.insert({identifier, identifiert{symbol.type(), true}});
5047 shadowed_syms.insert(
5048 {identifier,
5049 id_entry.second ? std::nullopt
5050 : std::optional{id_entry.first->second}});
5051 }
5052 find_symbols(q_expr.where());
5053 for(const auto &[id, shadowed_val] : shadowed_syms)
5054 {
5055 auto previous_entry = identifier_map.find(id);
5056 if(!shadowed_val.has_value())
5057 identifier_map.erase(previous_entry);
5058 else
5059 previous_entry->second = std::move(*shadowed_val);
5060 }
5061 return;
5062 }
5063
5064 // recursive call on operands
5065 for(const auto &op : expr.operands())
5066 find_symbols(op);
5067
5068 if(expr.id()==ID_symbol ||
5069 expr.id()==ID_nondet_symbol)
5070 {
5071 // we don't track function-typed symbols
5072 if(expr.type().id()==ID_code)
5073 return;
5074
5075 irep_idt identifier;
5076
5077 if(expr.id()==ID_symbol)
5078 identifier=to_symbol_expr(expr).get_identifier();
5079 else
5080 identifier="nondet_"+
5081 id2string(to_nondet_symbol_expr(expr).get_identifier());
5082
5083 auto id_entry =
5084 identifier_map.insert({identifier, identifiert{expr.type(), false}});
5085
5086 if(id_entry.second)
5087 {
5088 std::string smt2_identifier=convert_identifier(identifier);
5089 smt2_identifiers.insert(smt2_identifier);
5090
5091 out << "; find_symbols\n";
5092 out << "(declare-fun " << smt2_identifier;
5093
5094 if(expr.type().id() == ID_mathematical_function)
5095 {
5096 auto &mathematical_function_type =
5097 to_mathematical_function_type(expr.type());
5098 out << " (";
5099 bool first = true;
5100
5101 for(auto &type : mathematical_function_type.domain())
5102 {
5103 if(first)
5104 first = false;
5105 else
5106 out << ' ';
5107 convert_type(type);
5108 }
5109
5110 out << ") ";
5111 convert_type(mathematical_function_type.codomain());
5112 }
5113 else
5114 {
5115 out << " () ";
5116 convert_type(expr.type());
5117 }
5118
5119 out << ")" << "\n";
5120 }
5121 }
5122 else if(expr.id() == ID_array_of)
5123 {
5124 if(!use_as_const)
5125 {
5126 if(defined_expressions.find(expr) == defined_expressions.end())
5127 {
5128 const auto &array_of = to_array_of_expr(expr);
5129 const auto &array_type = array_of.type();
5130
5131 const irep_idt id =
5132 "array_of." + std::to_string(defined_expressions.size());
5133 out << "; the following is a substitute for lambda i. x\n";
5134 out << "(declare-fun " << id << " () ";
5135 convert_type(array_type);
5136 out << ")\n";
5137
5138 if(!is_zero_width(array_type.element_type(), ns))
5139 {
5140 // use a quantifier-based initialization instead of lambda
5141 out << "(assert (forall ((i ";
5142 convert_type(array_type.index_type());
5143 out << ")) (= (select " << id << " i) ";
5144 if(array_type.element_type().id() == ID_bool && !use_array_of_bool)
5145 {
5146 out << "(ite ";
5147 convert_expr(array_of.what());
5148 out << " #b1 #b0)";
5149 }
5150 else
5151 {
5152 convert_expr(array_of.what());
5153 }
5154 out << ")))\n";
5155 }
5156
5157 defined_expressions[expr] = id;
5158 }
5159 }
5160 }
5161 else if(expr.id() == ID_array_comprehension)
5162 {
5163 if(!use_lambda_for_array)
5164 {
5165 if(defined_expressions.find(expr) == defined_expressions.end())
5166 {
5167 const auto &array_comprehension = to_array_comprehension_expr(expr);
5168 const auto &array_type = array_comprehension.type();
5169 const auto &array_size = array_type.size();
5170
5171 const irep_idt id =
5172 "array_comprehension." + std::to_string(defined_expressions.size());
5173 out << "(declare-fun " << id << " () ";
5174 convert_type(array_type);
5175 out << ")\n";
5176
5177 out << "; the following is a substitute for lambda i . x(i)\n";
5178 out << "; universally quantified initialization of the array\n";
5179 out << "(assert (forall ((";
5180 convert_expr(array_comprehension.arg());
5181 out << " ";
5182 convert_type(array_size.type());
5183 out << ")) (=> (and (bvule (_ bv0 " << boolbv_width(array_size.type())
5184 << ") ";
5185 convert_expr(array_comprehension.arg());
5186 out << ") (bvult ";
5187 convert_expr(array_comprehension.arg());
5188 out << " ";
5189 convert_expr(array_size);
5190 out << ")) (= (select " << id << " ";
5191 convert_expr(array_comprehension.arg());
5192 out << ") ";
5193 if(array_type.element_type().id() == ID_bool && !use_array_of_bool)
5194 {
5195 out << "(ite ";
5196 convert_expr(array_comprehension.body());
5197 out << " #b1 #b0)";
5198 }
5199 else
5200 {
5201 convert_expr(array_comprehension.body());
5202 }
5203 out << "))))\n";
5204
5205 defined_expressions[expr] = id;
5206 }
5207 }
5208 }
5209 else if(expr.id()==ID_array)
5210 {
5211 if(defined_expressions.find(expr)==defined_expressions.end())
5212 {
5213 const array_typet &array_type=to_array_type(expr.type());
5214
5215 const irep_idt id = "array." + std::to_string(defined_expressions.size());
5216 out << "; the following is a substitute for an array constructor" << "\n";
5217 out << "(declare-fun " << id << " () ";
5218 convert_type(array_type);
5219 out << ")" << "\n";
5220
5221 if(!is_zero_width(array_type.element_type(), ns))
5222 {
5223 for(std::size_t i = 0; i < expr.operands().size(); i++)
5224 {
5225 out << "(assert (= (select " << id << " ";
5226 convert_expr(from_integer(i, array_type.index_type()));
5227 out << ") "; // select
5228 if(array_type.element_type().id() == ID_bool && !use_array_of_bool)
5229 {
5230 out << "(ite ";
5231 convert_expr(expr.operands()[i]);
5232 out << " #b1 #b0)";
5233 }
5234 else
5235 {
5236 convert_expr(expr.operands()[i]);
5237 }
5238 out << "))"
5239 << "\n"; // =, assert
5240 }
5241 }
5242
5243 defined_expressions[expr]=id;
5244 }
5245 }
5246 else if(expr.id()==ID_string_constant)
5247 {
5248 if(defined_expressions.find(expr)==defined_expressions.end())
5249 {
5250 // introduce a temporary array.
5251 exprt tmp=to_string_constant(expr).to_array_expr();
5252 const array_typet &array_type=to_array_type(tmp.type());
5253
5254 const irep_idt id =
5255 "string." + std::to_string(defined_expressions.size());
5256 out << "; the following is a substitute for a string" << "\n";
5257 out << "(declare-fun " << id << " () ";
5258 convert_type(array_type);
5259 out << ")" << "\n";
5260
5261 for(std::size_t i=0; i<tmp.operands().size(); i++)
5262 {
5263 out << "(assert (= (select " << id << ' ';
5264 convert_expr(from_integer(i, array_type.index_type()));
5265 out << ") "; // select
5266 convert_expr(tmp.operands()[i]);
5267 out << "))" << "\n";
5268 }
5269
5270 defined_expressions[expr]=id;
5271 }
5272 }
5273 else if(
5274 const auto object_size = expr_try_dynamic_cast<object_size_exprt>(expr))
5275 {
5276 if(object_sizes.find(*object_size) == object_sizes.end())
5277 {
5278 const irep_idt id = convert_identifier(
5279 "object_size." + std::to_string(object_sizes.size()));
5280 out << "(declare-fun " << id << " () ";
5281 convert_type(object_size->type());
5282 out << ")"
5283 << "\n";
5284
5285 object_sizes[*object_size] = id;
5286 }
5287 }
5288 // clang-format off
5289 else if(!use_FPA_theory &&
5290 expr.operands().size() >= 1 &&
5291 (expr.id() == ID_floatbv_plus ||
5292 expr.id() == ID_floatbv_minus ||
5293 expr.id() == ID_floatbv_mult ||
5294 expr.id() == ID_floatbv_div ||
5295 expr.id() == ID_floatbv_typecast ||
5296 expr.id() == ID_ieee_float_equal ||
5297 expr.id() == ID_ieee_float_notequal ||
5298 ((expr.id() == ID_lt ||
5299 expr.id() == ID_gt ||
5300 expr.id() == ID_le ||
5301 expr.id() == ID_ge ||
5302 expr.id() == ID_isnan ||
5303 expr.id() == ID_isnormal ||
5304 expr.id() == ID_isfinite ||
5305 expr.id() == ID_isinf ||
5306 expr.id() == ID_sign ||
5307 expr.id() == ID_unary_minus ||
5308 expr.id() == ID_typecast ||
5309 expr.id() == ID_abs) &&
5310 to_multi_ary_expr(expr).op0().type().id() == ID_floatbv)))
5311 // clang-format on
5312 {
5313 irep_idt function =
5314 convert_identifier("float_bv." + expr.id_string() + floatbv_suffix(expr));
5315
5316 if(bvfp_set.insert(function).second)
5317 {
5318 out << "; this is a model for " << expr.id() << " : "
5319 << type2id(to_multi_ary_expr(expr).op0().type()) << " -> "
5320 << type2id(expr.type()) << "\n"
5321 << "(define-fun " << function << " (";
5322
5323 for(std::size_t i = 0; i < expr.operands().size(); i++)
5324 {
5325 if(i!=0)
5326 out << " ";
5327 out << "(op" << i << ' ';
5328 convert_type(expr.operands()[i].type());
5329 out << ')';
5330 }
5331
5332 out << ") ";
5333 convert_type(expr.type()); // return type
5334 out << ' ';
5335
5336 exprt tmp1=expr;
5337 for(std::size_t i = 0; i < tmp1.operands().size(); i++)
5338 tmp1.operands()[i]=
5339 smt2_symbolt("op"+std::to_string(i), tmp1.operands()[i].type());
5340
5341 exprt tmp2=float_bv(tmp1);
5342 tmp2=letify(tmp2);
5343 CHECK_RETURN(!tmp2.is_nil());
5344
5345 convert_expr(tmp2);
5346
5347 out << ")\n"; // define-fun
5348 }
5349 }
5350 else if(
5351 use_FPA_theory && expr.id() == ID_typecast &&
5352 to_typecast_expr(expr).op().type().id() == ID_floatbv &&
5353 expr.type().id() == ID_bv)

5355 // This is _NOT_ a semantic conversion, but bit-wise.
5356 if(defined_expressions.find(expr) == defined_expressions.end())

5359 // new bit-vector variable and then asserting that it converts
5360 // to the required floating-point number.

5366

5368 const auto &floatbv_type = to_floatbv_type(tc.op().type());
5369 out << "(assert (= ";
5370 out << "((_ to_fp " << floatbv_type.get_e() << " "
5371 << floatbv_type.get_f() + 1 << ") " << id << ')';
5372 convert_expr(tc.op());
5373 out << ')'; // =
5374 out << ')' << '\n';
5375
5376 defined_expressions[expr] = id;
5377 }
5378 }
5379 else if(expr.id() == ID_initial_state)
5380 {
5381 irep_idt function = "initial-state";
5382
5383 if(state_fkt_declared.insert(function).second)
5384 {
5385 out << "(declare-fun " << function << " (";
5386 convert_type(to_unary_expr(expr).op().type());
5387 out << ") ";
5388 convert_type(expr.type()); // return type
5389 out << ")\n"; // declare-fun
5390 }
5391 }
5392 else if(expr.id() == ID_evaluate)
5393 {
5394 irep_idt function = "evaluate-" + type2id(expr.type());
5395
5396 if(state_fkt_declared.insert(function).second)
5397 {
5398 out << "(declare-fun " << function << " (";
5399 convert_type(to_binary_expr(expr).op0().type());
5400 out << ' ';
5401 convert_type(to_binary_expr(expr).op1().type());
5402 out << ") ";
5403 convert_type(expr.type()); // return type
5404 out << ")\n"; // declare-fun
5405 }
5406 }
5407 else if(
5408 expr.id() == ID_state_is_cstring ||
5409 expr.id() == ID_state_is_dynamic_object ||
5410 expr.id() == ID_state_live_object || expr.id() == ID_state_writeable_object)
5411 {
5412 irep_idt function =
5413 expr.id() == ID_state_is_cstring ? "state-is-cstring"
5414 : expr.id() == ID_state_is_dynamic_object ? "state-is-dynamic-object"
5415 : expr.id() == ID_state_live_object ? "state-live-object"

5417
5418 if(state_fkt_declared.insert(function).second)
5419 {
5420 out << "(declare-fun " << function << " (";
5421 convert_type(to_binary_expr(expr).op0().type());
5422 out << ' ';
5423 convert_type(to_binary_expr(expr).op1().type());
5424 out << ") ";
5425 convert_type(expr.type()); // return type
5426 out << ")\n"; // declare-fun
5427 }
5428 }
5429 else if(
5430 expr.id() == ID_state_r_ok || expr.id() == ID_state_w_ok ||
5431 expr.id() == ID_state_rw_ok)
5432 {
5433 irep_idt function = expr.id() == ID_state_r_ok ? "state-r-ok"
5434 : expr.id() == ID_state_w_ok ? "state-w-ok"
5435 : "state-rw-ok";
5436
5437 if(state_fkt_declared.insert(function).second)
5438 {
5439 out << "(declare-fun " << function << " (";
5440 convert_type(to_ternary_expr(expr).op0().type());
5441 out << ' ';
5442 convert_type(to_ternary_expr(expr).op1().type());
5443 out << ' ';
5444 convert_type(to_ternary_expr(expr).op2().type());
5445 out << ") ";
5446 convert_type(expr.type()); // return type
5447 out << ")\n"; // declare-fun
5448 }
5449 }
5450 else if(expr.id() == ID_update_state)
5451 {
5452 irep_idt function =
5453 "update-state-" + type2id(to_multi_ary_expr(expr).op2().type());
5454
5455 if(state_fkt_declared.insert(function).second)
5456 {
5457 out << "(declare-fun " << function << " (";
5458 convert_type(to_multi_ary_expr(expr).op0().type());
5459 out << ' ';
5460 convert_type(to_multi_ary_expr(expr).op1().type());
5461 out << ' ';
5462 convert_type(to_multi_ary_expr(expr).op2().type());
5463 out << ") ";
5464 convert_type(expr.type()); // return type
5465 out << ")\n"; // declare-fun
5466 }

5593
5594bool smt2_convt::use_array_theory(const exprt &expr)
5595{
5596 const typet &type = expr.type();
5597 PRECONDITION(type.id()==ID_array);
5598
5599 // arrays inside structs get flattened, unless we have datatypes
5600 if(expr.id() == ID_with)
5601 return use_array_theory(to_with_expr(expr).old());
5602 else
5603 return use_datatypes || expr.id() != ID_member;
5604}
5605
5606void smt2_convt::convert_type(const typet &type)
5607{
5608 if(type.id()==ID_array)
5609 {
5610 const array_typet &array_type=to_array_type(type);
5611 CHECK_RETURN(array_type.size().is_not_nil());
5612
5613 // we always use array theory for top-level arrays
5614 const typet &subtype = array_type.element_type();
5615
5616 // Arrays map the index type to the element type.
5617 out << "(Array ";
5618 convert_type(array_type.index_type());
5619 out << " ";
5620
5621 if(subtype.id()==ID_bool && !use_array_of_bool)
5622 out << "(_ BitVec 1)";
5623 else
5624 convert_type(array_type.element_type());
5625
5626 out << ")";
5627 }
5628 else if(type.id()==ID_bool)
5629 {
5630 out << "Bool";
5631 }
5632 else if(type.id() == ID_struct || type.id() == ID_struct_tag)
5633 {
5634 if(use_datatypes)
5635 {
5636 out << datatype_map.at(type);
5637 }
5638 else
5639 {
5640 std::size_t width=boolbv_width(type);
5641
5642 out << "(_ BitVec " << width << ")";
5643 }
5644 }
5645 else if(type.id()==ID_code)
5646 {
5647 // These may appear in structs.
5648 // We replace this by "Bool" in order to keep the same
5649 // member count.
5650 out << "Bool";
5651 }
5652 else if(type.id() == ID_union || type.id() == ID_union_tag)
5653 {
5654 std::size_t width=boolbv_width(type);
5655 const union_typet &union_type = type.id() == ID_union_tag
5656 ? ns.follow_tag(to_union_tag_type(type))
5657 : to_union_type(type);
5658 CHECK_RETURN_WITH_DIAGNOSTICS(
5659 union_type.components().empty() || width != 0,
5660 "failed to get width of union");
5661
5662 out << "(_ BitVec " << width << ")";
5663 }
5664 else if(type.id()==ID_pointer)
5665 {
5666 out << "(_ BitVec "
5667 << boolbv_width(type) << ")";
5668 }
5669 else if(type.id()==ID_bv ||
5670 type.id()==ID_fixedbv ||
5671 type.id()==ID_unsignedbv ||
5672 type.id()==ID_signedbv ||
5673 type.id()==ID_c_bool)
5674 {
5675 out << "(_ BitVec "
5676 << to_bitvector_type(type).get_width() << ")";
5677 }
5678 else if(type.id()==ID_c_enum)
5679 {
5680 // these have an underlying type
5681 out << "(_ BitVec "
5682 << to_bitvector_type(to_c_enum_type(type).underlying_type()).get_width()
5683 << ")";
5684 }
5685 else if(type.id()==ID_c_enum_tag)
5686 {
5687 convert_type(ns.follow_tag(to_c_enum_tag_type(type)));
5688 }
5689 else if(type.id()==ID_floatbv)
5690 {
5691 const floatbv_typet &floatbv_type=to_floatbv_type(type);
5692
5693 if(use_FPA_theory)
5694 out << "(_ FloatingPoint "
5695 << floatbv_type.get_e() << " "
5696 << floatbv_type.get_f() + 1 << ")";
5697 else
5698 out << "(_ BitVec "
5699 << floatbv_type.get_width() << ")";
5700 }
5701 else if(type.id()==ID_rational ||
5702 type.id()==ID_real)
5703 out << "Real";
5704 else if(type.id()==ID_integer)
5705 out << "Int";
5706 else if(type.id()==ID_complex)
5707 {
5708 if(use_datatypes)
5709 {
5710 out << datatype_map.at(type);
5711 }
5712 else
5713 {
5714 std::size_t width=boolbv_width(type);
5715
5716 out << "(_ BitVec " << width << ")";
5717 }
5718 }
5719 else if(type.id()==ID_c_bit_field)
5720 {
5721 convert_type(c_bit_field_replacement_type(to_c_bit_field_type(type), ns));
5722 }
5723 else if(type.id() == ID_state)
5724 {
5725 out << "state";
5726 }
5727 else if(type.id() == ID_range)
5728 {
5729 auto &range_type = to_range_type(type);
5730 mp_integer size = range_type.get_to() - range_type.get_from() + 1;
5731 if(size <= 0)
5732 UNEXPECTEDCASE("unsuppored range type");
5733 out << "(_ BitVec " << address_bits(size) << ")";
5734 }
5735 else
5736 {
5737 UNEXPECTEDCASE("unsupported type: "+type.id_string());
5738 }
5739}
5740
5741void smt2_convt::find_symbols(const typet &type)
5742{
5743 std::set<irep_idt> recstack;
5744 find_symbols_rec(type, recstack);
5745}
5746
5747void smt2_convt::find_symbols_rec(
5748 const typet &type,
5749 std::set<irep_idt> &recstack)
5750{
5751 if(type.id()==ID_array)
5752 {
5753 const array_typet &array_type=to_array_type(type);
5754 find_symbols(array_type.size());
5755 find_symbols_rec(array_type.element_type(), recstack);
5756 }
5757 else if(type.id()==ID_complex)
5758 {
5759 find_symbols_rec(to_complex_type(type).subtype(), recstack);
5760
5761 if(use_datatypes &&
5762 datatype_map.find(type)==datatype_map.end())
5763 {
5764 const std::string smt_typename =
5765 "complex." + std::to_string(datatype_map.size());
5766 datatype_map[type] = smt_typename;
5767
5768 out << "(declare-datatypes ((" << smt_typename << " 0)) "
5769 << "(((mk-" << smt_typename;
5770
5771 out << " (" << smt_typename << ".imag ";
5772 convert_type(to_complex_type(type).subtype());
5773 out << ")";
5774
5775 out << " (" << smt_typename << ".real ";
5776 convert_type(to_complex_type(type).subtype());
5777 out << ")";
5778
5779 out << "))))\n";
5780 }
5781 }
5782 else if(type.id() == ID_struct)
5783 {
5784 // Cater for mutually recursive struct types
5785 bool need_decl=false;
5786 if(use_datatypes &&
5787 datatype_map.find(type)==datatype_map.end())
5788 {
5789 const std::string smt_typename =
5790 "struct." + std::to_string(datatype_map.size());
5791 datatype_map[type] = smt_typename;
5792 need_decl=true;
5793 }
5794
5795 const struct_typet::componentst &components =
5796 to_struct_type(type).components();
5797
5798 for(const auto &component : components)
5799 find_symbols_rec(component.type(), recstack);
5800
5801 // Declare the corresponding SMT type if we haven't already.
5802 if(need_decl)
5803 {
5804 const std::string &smt_typename = datatype_map.at(type);
5805
5806 // We're going to create a datatype named something like `struct.0'.
5807 // It's going to have a single constructor named `mk-struct.0' with an
5808 // argument for each member of the struct. The declaration that
5809 // creates this type looks like:
5810 //
5811 // (declare-datatypes ((struct.0 0)) (((mk-struct.0
5812 // (struct.0.component1 type1)
5813 // ...
5814 // (struct.0.componentN typeN)))))
5815 out << "(declare-datatypes ((" << smt_typename << " 0)) "
5816 << "(((mk-" << smt_typename << " ";
5817
5818 for(const auto &component : components)
5819 {
5820 if(is_zero_width(component.type(), ns))
5821 continue;
5822
5823 out << "(" << smt_typename << "." << component.get_name()
5824 << " ";
5825 convert_type(component.type());
5826 out << ") ";
5827 }
5828
5829 out << "))))" << "\n";
5830
5831 // Let's also declare convenience functions to update individual
5832 // members of the struct whil we're at it. The functions are
5833 // named like `update-struct.0.component1'. Their declarations
5834 // look like:
5835 //
5836 // (declare-fun update-struct.0.component1
5837 // ((s struct.0) ; first arg -- the struct to update
5838 // (v type1)) ; second arg -- the value to update
5839 // struct.0 ; the output type
5840 // (mk-struct.0 ; build the new struct...
5841 // v ; the updated value
5842 // (struct.0.component2 s) ; retain the other members
5843 // ...
5844 // (struct.0.componentN s)))
5845
5846 for(struct_union_typet::componentst::const_iterator
5847 it=components.begin();
5848 it!=components.end();
5849 ++it)
5850 {
5851 if(is_zero_width(it->type(), ns))
5852 continue;
5853
5854 const struct_union_typet::componentt &component=*it;
5855 out << "(define-fun update-" << smt_typename << "."
5856 << component.get_name() << " "
5857 << "((s " << smt_typename << ") "
5858 << "(v ";
5859 convert_type(component.type());
5860 out << ")) " << smt_typename << " "
5861 << "(mk-" << smt_typename
5862 << " ";
5863
5864 for(struct_union_typet::componentst::const_iterator
5865 it2=components.begin();
5866 it2!=components.end();
5867 ++it2)
5868 {
5869 if(it==it2)
5870 out << "v ";
5871 else if(!is_zero_width(it2->type(), ns))
5872 {
5873 out << "(" << smt_typename << "."
5874 << it2->get_name() << " s) ";
5875 }
5876 }
5877
5878 out << "))" << "\n";
5879 }
5880
5881 out << "\n";
5882 }
5883 }
5884 else if(type.id() == ID_union)
5885 {
5886 const union_typet::componentst &components =
5887 to_union_type(type).components();
5888
5889 for(const auto &component : components)
5890 find_symbols_rec(component.type(), recstack);
5891 }
5892 else if(type.id()==ID_code)
5893 {
5894 const code_typet::parameterst &parameters=
5895 to_code_type(type).parameters();
5896 for(const auto &param : parameters)
5897 find_symbols_rec(param.type(), recstack);
5898
5899 find_symbols_rec(to_code_type(type).return_type(), recstack);
5900 }
5901 else if(type.id()==ID_pointer)
5902 {
5903 find_symbols_rec(to_pointer_type(type).base_type(), recstack);
5904 }
5905 else if(type.id() == ID_struct_tag)
5906 {
5907 const auto &struct_tag = to_struct_tag_type(type);
5908 const irep_idt &id = struct_tag.get_identifier();
5909
5910 if(recstack.find(id) == recstack.end())
5911 {
5912 const auto &base_struct = ns.follow_tag(struct_tag);
5913 recstack.insert(id);
5914 find_symbols_rec(base_struct, recstack);
5915 datatype_map[type] = datatype_map[base_struct];
5916 }
5917 }
5918 else if(type.id() == ID_union_tag)
5919 {
5920 const auto &union_tag = to_union_tag_type(type);
5921 const irep_idt &id = union_tag.get_identifier();
5922
5923 if(recstack.find(id) == recstack.end())
5924 {
5925 recstack.insert(id);
5926 find_symbols_rec(ns.follow_tag(union_tag), recstack);
5927 }
5928 }
5929 else if(type.id() == ID_state)
5930 {
5931 if(datatype_map.find(type) == datatype_map.end())
5932 {
5933 datatype_map[type] = "state";
5934 out << "(declare-sort state 0)\n";
5935 }
5936 }
5937 else if(type.id() == ID_mathematical_function)
5938 {
5939 const auto &mathematical_function_type =
5940 to_mathematical_function_type(type);
5941 for(auto &d_type : mathematical_function_type.domain())
5942 find_symbols_rec(d_type, recstack);
5943
5944 find_symbols_rec(mathematical_function_type.codomain(), recstack);
5945 }
5946}
